(180, 16, 'Stekt Torsk med Indisk smak', 2, 'no', '', 'Gurkemeie er et fantastisk krydder som ikke brukes ofte nok i norsk matlaging. Krydderet har en naturlig betennelsesdempende effekt. Sort pepper hjelper kroppen &aring; absorbere det aktive virkestoffet i gurkemeie (curcumin).', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland sammen krydderet i en skÃ¥l. Dekk fisken med krydderblandingen.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>VarmÂ en spiseskje olje i en stekepanne til middels varme.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>StekÂ torsken til den er gylden og gjennomstekt. For tynne filÃ©er sÃ¥ tar det ca 1-2 minutter per side og tykke filÃ©er ca 3-5 minutter per side. Torsken er ferdig hvis den flaker seg nÃ¥r du trykker lett pÃ¥ den.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med kokosris, grÃ¸nnsaker og oppkuttede gulerÃ¸tter.<br /><br />NÃ¥r du steker fisk sÃ¥ er det lurt Ã¥ ha den ute av kjÃ¸leskapet i 15-30 minutter sÃ¥ temperaturen i pannen ikke forandres nÃ¥r den stekes. Stek ogsÃ¥ fisken med siden som har vÃ¦rt eller har skinn pÃ¥ fÃ¸rst.Â </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '180.jpg', '180-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-01-13', '13:52:15', 7, 0, 0, '0', 1148, '192.99.9.25\n2a01:4f8:161:62d1::2\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n204.12.226.26\n173.212.247.190\n2607:5300:60:3b2f::1', 1, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', '', 'bfc3d35b398fc4898c13109d2b3e45de89e6b877', '2020-12-26 18:33:23', 0),
(183, 16, 'Eggehviteomelett', 1, 'no', '', 'En kalorifattig erstatning for omelett men full av proteiner! Topp gjerne den med litt basilkum, fetaost eller mozzarella.', '<ul><li>\r\n<p>Steg 1</p>\r\n<p>Kutt opp tomat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 2</p>\r\n<p>Skill eggehviten fra eggeplommen og pisk eggehviten med Ã¸nsket mengde salt og pepper i.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 3</p>\r\n<p>Ha litt olje i en stekepanne og varm til middels varme. Husk Ã¥ legge til ekstra kalorier i det totale nÃ¦ringsinnholdet avhenging av hvor mye olje du bruker.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 4</p>\r\n<p>Hell egghviten i stekepannen,Â  dekk pannen med et lokk og la steke i ett minutt.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 5</p>\r\n<p>Plasser tomater og spinat pÃ¥ den ene siden av omeletten og stek i to til tre minutter.Â Brett omeletten i halv med en spatel og stek i ytterligere to-tre minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul><p>Server med hot-sauce, grovt brÃ¸d og grÃ¸nnsaker.Â </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/2/2019', '183.jpg', '183-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-01-14', '13:42:25', 0, 0, 0, '0', 700, '185.191.171.43\n192.99.9.25\n2a01:4f8:161:62d1::2\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.21\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n192.99.13.75\n62.138.2.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', '', '6622cce208c44b62c81cd8f96a1bbe1663d09c9d', '2020-12-27 03:02:54', 0),
(184, 16, 'Sitron Kylling Wok', 2, 'no', '', 'Hvem visste at sitron fungerer s&aring; bra i wok? Sunt, godt og enkelt!', '<ul><li>\r\n<p>Steg 1</p>\r\n<p>Juice en halv sitron i en bolle, tilsett soyasaus, buljong og maisstivelse. RÃ¸r godt sammen. Riv skallet av sitronen og sett det til sides.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 2</p>\r\n<p>Hak gulrÃ¸tter, vÃ¥rlÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k og sopp i Ã¸nsket fasong. SkjÃ¦r kyllingen i tynne striper eller terninger.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 3</p>\r\n<p>Stek kyllingen i en stekepanne til den er ferdig, ca 4-5 minutter.Â  VÃ¦r oppmerksom pÃ¥ a legge til ekstra kalorier til nÃ¦ringsinnholdet hvis du bruker olje. Legg kyllingen til sides pÃ¥ et fat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 4</p>\r\n<p>I samme panne stek sopp og gulrÃ¸tter til de er myke, ca 4 minutter. Ha sÃ¥ i vÃ¥rlÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k, 0.5 teskje av sitronskall og sukker erterene. Stek i et minutt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 5</p>\r\n<p>RÃ¸r i sausen og tilsett den ilag med grÃ¸nnsakene og la koke sammen til den blir tykkere, ca 2-3 minutter. Tilsett kyllingen, rÃ¸r til den er dekket av saus og er gjennomvarm i ca 1-2 minutter.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul><p>Server med ris eller squash nudler. Topp med knust rÃ¸d pepper.Â </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '184.jpeg', '184-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-01-14', '15:54:20', 2, 0, 0, '0', 964, '192.99.9.25\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.158.241\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n2a01:4f8:200:814b::2\n2607:5300:60:3b2f::1', 0, '81.166.21.244', '', '8128e60cc4ae6382049e402e5373c0d638dfb512', '2020-12-26 18:37:12', 0),
(185, 2, 'Coffee Light frappuccino', 7, 'no', '', 'Inspirert av Starbucks! Lager to store glass.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland sammen alt i en blender og server!&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Xanthan gum hjelper for &aring; holde&nbsp;flytende v&aelig;ske tyktflytende og at konsistensen p&aring; drikken blir riktig. Xanthan gum har ingenting med smaken &aring; gj&oslash;re s&aring; du kan lage den uten, men frappuccinoen blir ikke like godt blandet. Annen melk kan &aring; brukes.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/7/3/2019', '185.jpeg', '185_thumb_278x184.png', '', '2019-01-21', '13:10:09', 0, 0, 0, '', 1182, '192.99.9.25\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n2a01:4f8:200:814b::2\n2607:5300:60:3b2f::1\n2607:5300:60:37e2::1\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:4449::2', 0, '81.166.21.244', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b403e7ab3dfa01f9550f779c19efb7c5c3ade64e', '2020-12-26 18:39:05', 0),
(186, 16, 'Moussaka', 2, 'no', '', 'Moussaka med en sunn vri!', '<ul><li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Forvarm ovnen til 200 grader.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk lÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k, sopp, aubergine, tomat, og paprika i terninger.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brun karbonadedeigen i en stekepanne.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett lÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k og sjampinjong, stek i 2 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett aubergine, paprika, timian, og stekÂ  i ca 4 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 6</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett bÃ¸nner, tomat, tomatsaus, en halvÂ buljong terning og krydderet: la smÃ¥koke i 5 minutter. Hvis sausen tÃ¸rk inn, fyll pÃ¥ litt vann, ca 1 dl.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 7</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hell alt over i en ildfastÂ form.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 8</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kombiner yoghurt og egg godt i en bolle. Ha over blandingen i den ildfaste formen.Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 9</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake iÂ stekeovn i 12-14 minutter, til den blir lysebrun pÃ¥ toppen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul><p>Server med en grÃ¸nn salat ogÂ ferskt brÃ¸d.Â Dryss gjerne over med persille.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '186.jpeg', '186-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-01-21', '16:17:30', 6, 0, 0, '0', 1085, '192.99.9.25\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:8046::2\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n62.138.2.243\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f8:161:9067::2\n2607:5300:60:3b2f::1\n2607:5300:60:37e2::1', 6, '81.166.21.244', '', '5bc4ddd13291db7e42a43355191c8a5b77d934bd', '2020-12-26 18:40:19', 0),
(187, 3, 'Cherry Oat Bars', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'I love cherry and oats. Combining both brings upon a whole new level of desserts. Can be customized by using less sugar or replacing sugar with sugar-substitutes. To save time, make the cherry filling one or two days before and store in the fridge in an airtight container.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350&deg;F.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Line a 9x9 pan with parchment paper and lightly grease it. If you want a thinner crust, use a 9x13 pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make the cherry filling by combining cherries, cornstarch, and sugar in a pot. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes stirring frequently.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Crush cornflakes then combine all crust ingredients in a large bowl until it becomes soft and crumbly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pat 2/3rd of the crust into the parchment covered pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 6</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover the crust with the cherry filling using a slotted spoon. Careful that you do not transfer too much of the liquid from the cherry filling to avoid the crust from getting soggy. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 7</strong></p>\r\n<p>Crumble the rest of the crust mixture over the cherry mixture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 8</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake for 30 minutes. Let cool before cutting into 12 bars, enjoy!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Store in the fridge in an airtight container for 2-3 days.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '187.jpeg', '187-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-01-29', '07:24:38', 0, 0, 0, '', 1911, '192.99.9.25\n192.99.5.225\n185.191.171.11\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n185.191.171.42\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2', 0, '2605:e000:614d:6100:1d4e:be79:7c9e:1070', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '526fef1a3f655aab5e4c0b76e9138c787c5d0a26', '2020-12-26 18:42:12', 0),
(192, 1, 'Fersk pasta', 6, 'no', 'Norway', 'Tagliatelle f&aring;r du kj&oslash;pt fersk p&aring; supermarkedene.', '', '', '', '', '', '2019-02-16', '09:56:50', 0, 0, 0, '', 1, '193.214.73.246', 0, '193.214.73.246', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c13f3342d3ab1e10dc26abe6c95fe2f0e97dd085', '2019-03-07 21:37:12', 0),
(193, 3, 'English Muffin with Egg White &amp; Cheese', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Microwave your egg white for a quick breakfast or lunch. For more protein add a slice of turkey sausage or ham!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Toast the muffin to your liking.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour the egg white into a microwave safe dish that is the same size as the muffin.&nbsp; Add salt and pepper if you want.&nbsp; Microwave for 30-90 seconds depending on your microwave.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Assemble the muffin with spinach, egg white, and cheese.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a cup of soup or salad. Goes well with sliced tomato and a bit butter as well.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br />Feel free to use a bagel thin, sandwich thin, or bread instead of a muffin.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '193.jpeg', '193-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-02-28', '19:18:52', 1, 0, 0, '', 1259, '161.97.136.234\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n192.99.13.75\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n173.212.247.190\n2a01:4f8:161:9067::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:980:b041:bb0b:a0eb', '', '8c27307678b380b362443ae7dcc8f1f11990d2c3', '2020-12-27 06:38:25', 0),
(194, 3, 'Shrimp in yogurt sauce with pasta', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'One of my favorite shrimp recipes. Feel free to substitute green beans for asparagus or cilantro for parsley.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">Bring a pot of water to boil, add spaghetti and cook. Slice bell pepper and the green beans. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">When there are two minutes remaining on the pasta add shrimp, green beans and bell pepper. You might have to let the spaghetti boil another minute. Drain the pasta and vegetables. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">Chop garlic and cilantro. In a small bowl mix yogurt, cilantro, and lemon juice.&nbsp; Toss the pasta with the sauce and serve. <br />Add salt and pepper to taste. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\"><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">If you are using raw shrimp, let them boil with the pasta for a total of 3-4 minutes. </span></span><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">Be careful to not overcook them as shrimp cook quickly. They will turn pink and form a loose C shape when they are done. If they start curling to tighter O shape they are overcooked.</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '194.jpeg', '194-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-01', '02:27:36', 24, 0, 0, '', 1236, '185.191.171.45\n185.191.171.19\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n167.114.159.99\n185.191.171.37\n185.191.171.17\n62.138.2.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:885c:a8ea:45d5:484d', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '21203dce4ad6609f8693c92534ea5f42e0fd6e2b', '2020-12-26 19:37:58', 0),
(195, 3, 'Apple Pie Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Dessert for breakfast that is healthy? Yes, please!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the apple. Add apple and vanilla extract to the oatmeal and stir well. Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as chopped walnuts, banana, allspice, ground ginger, or brown sugar.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\">I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '195.jpeg', '195-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-08', '03:16:16', 0, 0, 0, '', 1409, '185.191.171.37\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n185.191.171.11\n114.119.129.199\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a4a2:b93e:657e:14c8', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bb60ee4dc8ecd98c7f79ebdcac7a32f1050ae91a', '2020-12-26 23:25:35', 0),
(198, 3, 'Skinny Pesto Chicken Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A tasty soup that literally makes itself in a slow cooker.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the vegetables, basil, and garlic.&nbsp; For the chicken, you can either chop it now or cook the entire breast and chop/shred it after the soup is cooked. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all the ingredients except for the parmesan in a two-quart slow cooker and stir.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover and cook for 3-4 hours on high or 7-8 hours on low.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop or shred the chicken breast if you cooked it as a whole and return to the soup. Stir in parmesan and serve. Add salt and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '198.jpg', '198-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-16', '01:59:24', 22, 0, 0, '', 857, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n185.191.171.7\n185.191.171.9\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'af0573e93d60ee57fa4dd47440d092b034ec132d', '2020-12-26 12:32:01', 0),
(199, 3, 'Frozen Yogurt', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and high in protein. In the photo, I added a Fiber One Brownie and four crushed mini Oreo cookies.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Mix together the ingredients using a hand mixer on medium speed for a couple of minutes. This help add air and volume into the ice cream.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.</p>\r\n<strong>If you do not have an ice cream maker you can use one of these three options. It will not yield the same result but still delicious:</strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Freeze the mixture until semi-frozen in \"blender friendly sizes\" and then use a blender to get the right consistency.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Freeze the mixture in a container that you stir every 30 minutes for around 2 hours.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">You can also mold it into pop sticks or make Greek yogurt bark, see this recipe: <a class=\"s1w8oh2o-27 tTnje\" href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=169\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=169</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>My usual batch. One serving, 400 gram of delicious vanilla frozen yogurt</strong><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190404062928.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"635\" height=\"847\" /><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Topped with homemade three berry blend jam:</strong><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190404062941.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2825\" height=\"3697\" /><br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '199.jpg', '199-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-16', '05:32:45', 0, 0, 0, '', 1729, '185.191.171.8\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.25\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243\n178.151.245.174\n185.191.171.7\n2a01:4f8:161:9067::2', 0, '142.129.116.49', '', '07839cd8a808b3cc0f0857ac47fc3e21e9bfb7a6', '2020-12-26 12:38:20', 0),
(200, 3, 'Taco with spaghetti squash', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'One of my favorite dinners. Switch up your regular Friday tacos with this tasty and healthy recipe! Feel free to use ground turkey or chicken instead of ground beef.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Roast the spaghetti squash, <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=52&amp;l=en\">if you don\'t know how to: follow this guide</a>. When it is done, use a fork to scoop out two servings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>After the spaghetti squash is done, brown the ground beef in a skillet. Add water according to the package and two servings of the spice mix. If you use McCormick Taco Seasoning add 120 ml (0.5 cups) water and 9 gram (4 tsp) spice mix.&nbsp; Let simmer 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the two servings of the spaghetti squash to the skillet and stir to combine with the ground beef.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with your favorite taco toppings. I use finely chopped romaine lettuce, bell peppers, cilantro, jalapeno, chopped green onions. Other ideas are Mexican shredded cheese, pico de gallo or salsa, avocado, lime, sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '200.jpeg', '200-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-16', '22:47:43', 14, 0, 0, '', 1182, '185.191.171.39\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n62.138.2.243\n178.151.245.174\n185.191.171.19\n185.191.171.45', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f8e0:f1c7:d34:1805', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0ea4c16b1fa04558510613d166f641168fbb1a1c', '2020-12-26 01:41:29', 0),
(201, 3, 'Hot Cocoa Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Taste like hot cocoa, indulgent and healthy!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water,&nbsp; and cocoa (Dutch processed) in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as marshmallows, banana, powdered peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong>I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. </span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '201.jpeg', '201-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-19', '16:26:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 1332, '192.99.5.225\n114.119.129.199\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.17\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n192.99.13.75\n37.57.218.243\n185.191.171.12', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:40b:3010:cb92:e08d', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '23d1d035f9ac4cebca196f004c7f8c1e18969c38', '2020-12-26 12:34:52', 0),
(202, 3, 'Berry Smoothie Bowl', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'The best smoothie bowls are dense like a bowl of healthy sorbet. This is an easy recipe for a smoothie bowl that only needs three ingredients!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut and freeze banana a few hours before making the smoothie bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the ingredients in a blender and blend to a puree.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a deep bowl and top with your favorite toppings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Tips for a better smoothie bowl:<br />- Add a tablespoon&nbsp; Greek yogurt for extra creaminess. <br />- Add sweeteners to your smoothie bowl as frozen fruits usually lose their sweetness.<br />- A good blender will make all the difference in the consistency of your smoothie bowl. Usually, the cheaper blenders will leave your smoothie bowl more chunky or grainy.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '202.jpeg', '202-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-22', '17:40:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1146, '114.119.137.125\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.9\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.26', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:50b0:e459:70b8:6bd2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '45fb71eb8900fbc540de35a4e58dadcda78e66fc', '2020-12-27 04:47:28', 0),
(203, 3, 'Lemon and Dill Oven Baked Salmon', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Oven baked salmon is super healthy and so easy to make!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray an oven-safe pan with non-stick spray or line with aluminum foil/parchment paper.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make the lemon marinade by mixing all the ingredients into a bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the salmon into the pan and coat the filets with the lemon marinade.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 6</strong><br /><br />Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes, depending on the thickness of your fillets. The salmon is done when it can easily be flaked with a fork.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with steamed vegetables and rice.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '203.jpeg', '203-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-23', '00:06:06', 24, 0, 0, '', 1006, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n62.138.2.243\n185.191.171.4\n178.151.245.174', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c40f:2a08:f1c0:3b36', '', '1aa15cbd9f0b1f8f6734d9ff28fc9f6c53c464be', '2020-12-26 12:38:23', 0),
(204, 3, 'Red Bell Pepper Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I love the simplicity of this soup. No need to roast, peel, and steam the bell pepper. Everything can be made in one pan, easy and delicious.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Remove the seeds from the bell pepper. Chop the bell pepper, onion, and garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Saut&eacute; the bell pepper, onion and garlic in a pot for 10 min. I saut&eacute; mine in water, but you can use non-stick spray, butter, or oil. Remember that the overall caloric nutrition changes then.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken stock and let simmer for 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Use an immersion blender or heat-safe blender to puree the soup and serve.&nbsp; Add salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a tablespoon greek yogurt or sour cream stirred in. Top with fresh cilantro, chopped green onions, cheese, croutons, or bacon.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '204.jpeg', '204-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-23', '00:28:51', 0, 0, 0, '', 1079, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c40f:2a08:f1c0:3b36', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2811734006177e2e596eacb6472536cfa3f91d66', '2020-12-26 12:39:39', 0),
(205, 3, 'Jicama Fries', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Jicama has a neutral taste that soaks up flavors from spices. High in fiber and paleo, low carb, or keto friendly.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the&nbsp;jicama into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat air fryer to 400 F or oven to 400 F.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a large bowl mix together the spices and jicama. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the jicama with spices and oil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Place jicama strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30-45 minutes. <br /><br /><strong>Air fryer</strong><br />Place the jicama strips in a single layer in the basket and cook for 20 minutes. Shake the basket or turn the jicama strips every 5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.&nbsp; If you like garlic add 1/4th teaspoon garlic and onion powder to the spice mix in step 3. For a spicy twist, add 1/4th teaspoon chili powder!<br /><br /><strong>For a potato fry-like texture boil the jicama strips for 10-15 minutes and pat dry before air frying.</strong></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '205.jpeg', '205-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-24', '04:47:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1232, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243\n2a01:4f8:162:8b::2\n2607:5300:120:36c::1\n2607:5300:60:3e85::1\n173.212.247.190', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:4d24:1ffc:a3e7:d7c4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'eb3a71a2e4eed779a2b7514b3c598e761a0d4f16', '2020-12-26 12:43:02', 0),
(206, 3, 'Skinny Mashed Cauliflower', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'A super-healthy and low-calorie substitute for mashed potatoes, rice or pasta. Top with chopped fresh chives and parmesan cheese.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the cauliflower into smaller pieces.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Boil the cauliflower in a saucepan with water until it gets tender, about 10 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour out the water and mash the cauliflower with a stick blender, blender, or by hand using a potato masher.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add milk and stir until you get desired consistency, I use 30 gram of non-fat milk. Season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can replace milk with water in step 4, use the same water that you boiled the cauliflower in. Goes well with some finely chopped garlic added in step 4 as well.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '206.jpeg', '206-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-24', '21:39:49', 0, 0, 0, '', 1043, '112.113.155.252\n2a01:4f8:192:214e::2\n2a01:4f8:212:5da::2\n2a01:4f8:200:54aa::2\n89.163.242.108\n2a01:4f8:201:6390::2\n91.53.44.44', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0b95bdd0b49471e4bc34a1a629a0b6c8e36a1b70', '2020-03-21 18:00:08', 0),
