(208, 16, 'Buffalo Kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Server som taco p&aring; tynne mais tortillas, som finger mat med selleri, eller over en salat.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â Bland ketchup og chili saus i en bolle stor nok til Ã¥ ha kyllingen i.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>SkjÃ¦r kylling til Ã¸nsket stÃ¸rrelse, for eksempel striper eller kuber.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stek kylling i en panne til den er ferdig, ca 5 minutter. Hvis du bruker olje- eller non-stick spray, vÃ¦r oppmerksom pÃ¥ at nÃ¦ringsverdien endres nÃ¥r jeg lager maten i vann.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland kyllingen i bollen med chili-sausen til den er belagt. Tilsett salt og pepper etter smak.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med gresk yoghurt eller rÃ¸mme, og selleripinner. <br /><br />Lag gjerne dobbel porsjon av oppskriften sÃ¥ kan du bruke den til lunsj i salat i morgen.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '208.jpeg', '208-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-12', '02:09:05', 1, 0, 0, '0', 1091, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '64f555d02dcdc5b56c11e66de8326464a76d1df3', '2020-12-27 04:02:27', 0),
(209, 16, 'Bakt laks i aluminiumsfolie', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Dette er den enkleste m&aring;ten &aring; lage laks med en god smak som hele familien vil nyte.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â  Forvarm ovnen til 190 C grader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland alt krydder i en bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Plasser laks i aluminiumsfolie. Hell Â½ ss sitronjuice pÃ¥ hver av filetene og gni i krydderblandingen. Tett aluminiumsfolien.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Plasser filÃ¨tene pÃ¥ et stekeovnsplate eller ildfast form og sett i ovnen i 35 minutter eller til fisken er ferdig. Fisken er ferdig nÃ¥r det er lett Ã¥ flake med en gaffel.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med dampet brokkoli og ris.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '209.jpeg', '209-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-21', '02:19:22', 0, 0, 0, '0', 989, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n167.114.158.241\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243\n178.151.245.174\n2607:5300:60:3e85::1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5cc2c22fe96f1b87bd3e67824697a92658ca8ca2', '2020-12-26 12:47:13', 0),
(210, 16, 'Luksus fiskesuppe', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En spennende fiskesuppe, overfylt med smak! Jeg bruker torsk i min, men du kan bruke annen fisk.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vask, skrell og kutt grÃ¸nnsakene i terninger.Â </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kutt fisken i biter.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kok opp 7 dl vann med grÃ¸nnsaksbuljongen og hakkede tomater i en gryte. Ha i krydderet, nepe, sopp, paprika, og lÃ¸ken.Â  La suppen koke i 5 minutter. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ha i fisken og squash . La fisken trekke i et par minutter til den er ferdig, ca 3-5 minutter. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med et godt brÃ¸d.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '210.jpeg', '210-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-02-12', '03:41:52', 24, 0, 0, '0', 850, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n62.138.2.243\n178.151.245.174', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5f62bd7dc52d76d171472f27cf55c3e02b33d1f3', '2020-12-26 12:57:16', 0),
(211, 16, 'Meksikansk picadillo', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En type meksikansk gryterett og en sunn middag som har uendelige muligheter.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk lÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k, koriander og gulrÃ¸tter i smÃ¥ terninger.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brun karbonadeig i en panne. NÃ¥r det er ca 4 minutter igjen av steketiden tilsett lÃ¸k og hvitlÃ¸k.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg til tomatsaus, gulrÃ¸tter, vann, Worcestershire saus og krydder.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dekk med et lokk og la smÃ¥koke til saus tykkere i 10-20 minutter. Hvis det blir for tykt, legg til mer vann.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serveres over en grÃ¸nn salat, mini tortillas, eller med ris.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '211.jpeg', '211-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-25', '04:13:45', 14, 0, 0, '0', 1055, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n192.99.13.75', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '944785978669b304790c68280e6bda02edfd8403', '2020-12-27 04:02:50', 0),
(212, 3, 'Fried Tilapia with Turmeric', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Turmeric is a wonderful spice because it has a natural anti-inflammatory effect. Black pepper helps the body absorb the active ingredient in turmeric (curcumin). Tasty and healthy!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix the spice together in a bowl. Cover the fish with the spice mixture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat the oil over medium heat in a frying pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fry the tilapia until it is golden and cooked through. For thin fillets, it takes about 1-2 minutes per side and thick fillets about 3-5 minutes per side. The fish is finished if it flakes when you lightly press it with a fork.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with rice, fresh vegetables, and grated carrots. <br /><br />When you fry fish, it is advisable to keep it out of the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes so that the temperature in the pan does not change when it is cooked. Also, fry the fish with the side did not have skin on first.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '212.jpeg', '212-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-03-26', '20:48:34', 7, 0, 0, '', 1127, '192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n144.91.125.96\n62.138.2.243\n2607:5300:60:3e85::1\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f8:161:9067::2\n2607:5300:60:3b2f::1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:44a:3ade:e5b9:35db', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6c350db7468361d02dafa52d5c157505f8eefc55', '2020-12-26 13:03:59', 0),
(213, 3, 'Chipotle Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Make your own bowl, salad, taco, or burrito at home! Tasty, healthy and customizable.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop the chipotle pepper and garlic by hand or in a mini food processor. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices and chipotle pepper in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breast with the paste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken it in the fridge after coating it with the spice paste. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a>&nbsp; </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '213.jpeg', '213-thumb.jpeg', '', '2019-02-27', '00:39:04', 14, 0, 0, '', 1997, '161.97.136.234\n167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121', 0, '46.30.210.139', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '093c2287fa3df4adfcd988a7c8e4767914075e41', '2020-12-27 06:38:36', 0),
(214, 3, 'Springtime Chicken Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Soups are perfect for spring because now is the time for the freshest flavors of your garden goodness. Fresh dill provides that holiday feeling.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the vegetables.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat the oil in a soup pot over medium-high. Add bell peppers and cook for 3 minutes. Add green onions and garlic, cook another 2 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken stock, paprika, celery and bring to a boil. Once boiling reduce the heat and let simmer 15-20 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add green beans, zucchini, and dill. Let simmer 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with 1/4th of a lime squeeze over into each bowl. Add pepper to taste.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '214.jpg', '214-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-28', '02:01:24', 0, 0, 0, '', 881, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.4\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n114.119.133.14\n144.91.125.96', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', '', '753dc0e8e3dbb8c70c00f1b114c161a2b114b9f8', '2020-12-27 04:03:50', 0),
(218, 3, 'Very Berry Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'On Friday&#039;s we wear pink! Instagram friendly and tasty oatmeal.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water, and berries in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for 6+ hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as maple syrup, chopped hazelnuts, bananas, or more berries. <br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /></strong><br />I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. </span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '218.jpg', '218-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-01', '00:58:10', 0, 0, 0, '', 999, '114.119.138.25\n167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n144.91.125.96\n62.138.2.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:19ac:cbb:3c34:143e', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fee341a59554a9deaec478d2e20357ea9ce11b86', '2020-12-27 09:33:05', 0),
(219, 16, 'Taco suppe', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Har du en taco craving, men vil spare kalorier? Denne suppen er perfekt! Sopp sparer kalorier, men du opplever fortsatt en solid biff smak.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk grÃ¸nnsakene i biter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brun karbonadedeig i en panne. NÃ¥r det er nesten ferdig, legg til lÃ¸k, sopp og paprika. Stek til karbonadedeigen er ferdig, ca 3-4 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"_3l3x _1n4g\">Tilsett resterende ingredienser i pannen. Kok opp og la smÃ¥koke i 15-20 minutter</span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server toppet med favoritt taco toppings. <br />Mine favoritter:<br />- Fersk hakket koriander<br />- Gresk yoghurt eller rÃ¸mme<br />- Revet meksikansk ost eller Queso Fresco <br />- Avokado eller Guacamole<br />- GrÃ¸nn lÃ¸k<br />- Skiver Jalapeno<br />- Salsa eller Pico de Gallo<br />- Mais<br /><br />Du kan erstatte karbonadedeig for andre kjÃ¸ttvarer som kalkun eller kylling. Ta gjerne med bÃ¸nner i denne suppen!</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '219.jpg', '219-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-26', '03:49:58', 14, 0, 0, '0', 810, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.14\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.21\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '1f41dfbac2cc6190f14f0ce75383141d76b2fc01', '2020-12-27 04:07:28', 0),
(220, 16, 'Tikka Masala med Kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Full av smak, men lavere i kalorier enn din tradisjonelle Tikka Masala. Juster chili-pulveret etter dine preferanser, for en ekstra krydret matrett tilsett en til teskje chili.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Â Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk lÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k, ingefÃ¦r, og kylling.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Varm oljen i en stekepanne, tilsett lÃ¸k og stek til den erÂ  gylden.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett ingefÃ¦ren, rÃ¸r om i noen minutter, og legg deretter hvitlÃ¸k og stek i et til minutt. Tilsett krydder og stek i ca 2 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>RÃ¸r i hakkede tomater og melk. SmÃ¥kok pÃ¥ lav varme til sausen tykner, ca 10 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett kylling og la koke i 10 - 15 minutter eller til kokt gjennom. Tilsett CrÃ¨me FraÃ®che mot slutten av koketiden. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med hakket fersk koriander og med Bamati Rice eller Naan.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '220.jpg', '220-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-28', '05:10:03', 7, 0, 0, '0', 831, '185.191.171.4\n185.191.171.34\n178.151.245.174\n185.191.171.21\n185.191.171.40\n185.191.171.44\n207.180.218.247\n185.191.171.22\n185.191.171.1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'd388fb8ffe24cbc09de4e0a1e80ceaea776bb422', '2020-12-26 15:58:44', 0),
(221, 16, 'Sommerens Kyllingsuppe', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Supper er perfekt p&aring; sommeren siden det er tiden for de ferskeste smakene av sesongens gr&oslash;nnsaker. Frisk dill gir suppen en oppkvikkende smak.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â Hakk grÃ¸nnsakene.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â Varm oljen i en panne, tilsett paprika og stek i 3 minutter. Legg til v<span dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"_3l3x\">Ã¥</span></span>rlÃ¸k og hvitlÃ¸k, stek iÂ  2 til minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett vann, buljong, kylling, paprika krydder, selleri og kok opp. NÃ¥r det koker reduserer varmen og la det smÃ¥koke i 15-20 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg til grÃ¸nne bÃ¸nner,Â  squash og dill. La smÃ¥koke i 3-5 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server medÂ  1/4 av lime presset over i hver bolle. Tilsett pepper etter smak.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '221.jpg', '221-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-03-29', '05:54:44', 0, 0, 0, '0', 807, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b852c631daf2f3a464576884c5f75f1a25bda56a', '2020-12-27 04:10:24', 0),
(222, 3, 'Zucchini and Mushroom Chicken Stir Fry', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Craving Panda Express without going out and the excessive sodium? Look no further!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop zucchini, and mushroom. Grate garlic, and ginger. Cut chicken into thin bite-size pieces and coat with cornstarch.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make the sauce by combining soy sauce, sugar substitute, and rice vinegar in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat sesame oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until it is done, 3-5 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken. Set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add zucchini, and mushroom into the skillet. Let cook for 5 minutes. Add garlic and ginger and let cook for another minute.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add back the chicken and sauce. Cook until sauce thickens, about 2-3 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over rice or cauliflower rice. Sprinkle over with sesame seeds.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '222.jpg', '222-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-02', '00:20:35', 2, 0, 0, '', 968, '167.114.64.97\n167.114.158.215\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.42\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n144.91.125.96\n2a01:4f8:191:2094::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7164:7899:b6cf:4ebc', '', 'b46f5a2cee7f525f8fac554006a9afb42917244e', '2020-12-27 04:14:33', 0),
(223, 3, 'How To: Collard Wraps', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Substitute your boring tortilla for a fancy and low-calorie collard wrap instead. Better than lettuce leaves because collard leaves are larger, more sturdy and more flexible. Unlike lettuce wraps, they fold up without breaking. Can be eaten raw or boiled. Boiling them for 30 seconds makes them more flexible. Only 8 calories each leaf.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wash the collards to remove grit or debris. Bring a large pot of water to boil and let simmer, add a dash salt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030217.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"655\" /><br /><br />Using a small knife such as a paring knife, remove the thick part of the middle stem so the stem is as flat as the rest of the collard leaf.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepare an ice bath by filling a large bowl with cold water and ice cubes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030347.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1090\" /><br /><br />Drop each collard leaf into the simmering water for 30 seconds. The longer it is in the simmering water, the softer it becomes. Using a pair of tongs move the leaf into an ice bath for 10 seconds.<br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030412.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1015\" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030434.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1135\" /><br />Pat dry with a kitchen towel. Store between paper towels/parchment or wax paper in the fridge for three days. <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030454.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"728\" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Top it with your favorite ingredients and roll it up like a burrito. To cut in half use a serrated knife.&nbsp;<br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030616.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1158\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030648.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1204\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030709.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1079\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The difference between boiled and raw collard leaves. Boiled on left, raw on right:</strong> <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030805.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"503\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '223.jpg', '223-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-02', '02:39:23', 0, 0, 0, '', 1056, '167.114.64.97\n167.114.158.215\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n62.138.2.243\n2607:5300:120:36c::1\n173.212.247.190\n192.99.4.163', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7164:7899:b6cf:4ebc', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fe73b2c554d7b3609c2f61d863f50472c21a4dad', '2020-12-27 04:15:45', 0),
(225, 3, 'Sliders with grilled pineapple', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious sliders! Grilled pineapple have a smoked sweetness while the lemon coleslaw balances the entire dish.', '<p><strong>Ketchup&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix together, lemon, apple vinegar, and ketchup. Set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Coleslaw</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Shred red cabbage, cut the spring onion, set aside 25 grams of spring onion for the sliders.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the lemon juice, apple vinegar, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix together red cabbage, 25 grams of spring onion and lemon dressing made in step 2.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Sliders</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix ground beef, 25 grams of chopped spring onions, salt, and pepper.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Form to 8 small burgers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fry each burger over medium-high heat for 2-3 minutes before turning it over and fry until it is cooked, about 1-2 minutes. Move the ready sliders to a plate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Pineapple</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut up the pineapple into 8 thin rings or squares.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Cook for about 1-2 minutes in the same skillet as you cooked the burgers in on one side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Then put together each slider with slider bread, brush on ketchup on the underside, have a slider on top, then a pineapple ring and finally coleslaw over that. Bon Appetit!</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/89/2019', '225.jpg', '225-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-03', '04:49:17', 1, 0, 0, '', 823, '2a01:4f8:192:734b::2\n2a01:4f8:192:8108::2\n204.12.220.106\n2a01:4f8:202:338a::2\n2a01:e0a:2c2:8e80:65ee:5755:298f:5af5\n192.99.37.116\n192.99.10.170\n2a01:4f8:a0:5385::2\n2a01:4f9:2a:150::2\n2001:41d0:8:1999::1\n2a01:4f8:161:9067::2', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f6365fccba030d0d769bd913390d26d769095a4e', '2020-03-03 23:28:43', 0),
(227, 3, 'Broccoli Puree', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'This recipe is inspired by a restaurant I went to while visiting Norway. I had cod alongside with broccoli puree. The flavor was so simple yet sophisticated so I decided to duplicate the recipe. It goes well with white fish, salmon, pork, and chicken.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"3c9jd-0-0\">Bring a large pot with water to boil. Add a dash of salt. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop broccoli into smaller pieces, use the leaves and stems. <span data-offset-key=\"65rm-0-0\">Add broccoli to the boiling water. Let boil rapidly <strong>under a lid</strong> for 6-8 minutes.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"bvlk0-0-0\">Strain the water, but keep a small amount in-case you want to make the puree thinner.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"bvlk0-0-0\">Mash the broccoli to a puree consistency with a blender that tolerates heat,&nbsp; an immersion blender, or by hand with a potato masher. Add salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with Tabasco and lime juice.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '227.jpg', '227-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', '05:01:11', 23, 0, 0, '', 1016, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n167.114.158.215\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243\n167.114.159.99', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bd9878dcbe684a01f9901daf5dc14ccf1c2d8bc9', '2020-12-27 04:18:53', 0),
(228, 3, 'Pear &amp; Cardamom Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'I love cardamom. Growing up my grandma would make the most wonderful cardamom buns. This got me thinking, would the same spices work in my morning oatmeal? Oh Yes!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the ginger and grate or chop the pear. Combine oats, water,&nbsp; cardamom, ginger, and pear in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as walnuts, banana, peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong>I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick.<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\"> See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /><br />Cardamom is a very powerful spice. Some might find the flavor overwhelming or soap like if you use too much so you might want to start out with 1/8th of a teaspoon and work your way up.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '228.jpg', '228-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', '06:41:37', 23, 0, 0, '', 1050, '161.97.136.234\n167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n167.114.158.215\n95.91.110.121\n2607:5300:60:3880::1', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '910f0975dd04b358c2f987dd38e61842a1d041f7', '2020-12-27 06:38:39', 0),
(229, 3, 'Shrimp, Green Beans and Gnocchi', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to use any Gnocchi. I used Trader Joe&#039;s famous Cauliflower Gnocchi in mine. You can substitute green beans for broccoli, bell pepper, or asparagus. Use fresh lemon juice for best result!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"562es-0-0\">Chop green beans and shallot.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"562es-0-0\">Cook gnocchi in a skillet for 6-10 minutes or according to directions on package. Transfer to a plate once done.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\">In the same skillet over medium-high heat, cook shallots for 1-2 minutes. Add green beans and broth, cook another 3-4 minutes. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\">If using raw shrimp, add shrimp and let simmer until shrimp is done. About 3-4 minutes, it should turn pink. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\">If using pre-cooked shrimp, let green beans, shallots, and broth simmer another 3 minutes. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"f9d2a-0-0\">Add pre-cooked shrimp (if using), gnocchi and lemon juice: let simmer until everything is heated through. Remove skillet from heat and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Serve after cheese has melted, 1-2 minutes.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with&nbsp;red peppers flakes, fresh basil or parsley.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '229.jpg', '229-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', '23:10:26', 9, 0, 0, '', 1103, '114.119.132.43\n192.99.9.25\n192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n62.138.2.243', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f0ef3f6935c217ee87607bf3d075d1e8096b590b', '2020-12-27 07:00:05', 0),
(230, 3, 'Kung Pao Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Did you know that Kung Pao Chicken was traditionally made with leeks? Here in the US, we have grown accustomed to a version containing green onions instead. I do not use peanuts in my recipe, but feel free to add 50 gram chopped peanuts to yours along with the other vegetables. Bamboo shoots can be substituted with water chestnuts or omitted.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop up the green onions, garlic, and chicken. Drain bamboo shoots.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Make the sauce by combining the ingredients in a small bowl. Set aside.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Toss the chicken in the chicken marinade ingredients. If you have time, let marinate in the fridge for 30 minutes.&nbsp; Pan fry over medium-high heat until chicken is fully cooked.&nbsp; Set aside on a plate. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the same skillet slowly heat up the sauce and add the green onions, garlic, bamboo shoots.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the chicken and toss to coat the sauce, cook until sauce thickens. About 2-3 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with steamed vegetables and rice.<br /><br />For a darker sauce, use dark soy sauce. You can substitute white wine for an equal amount of soy sauce.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '230.jpg', '230-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-06', '22:42:44', 2, 0, 0, '', 1472, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n62.138.2.243\n114.119.138.25', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5f05d97f8dcbc0214b14cac34dd1cb1f099c5dc7', '2020-12-26 13:22:43', 0),
(231, 3, 'Green Beans in Air Fryer', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'A spicy and simple recipe that makes a great side dish.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim ends off green beans and mince the garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Make the sauce by combining all the ingredients except green beans. Toss the green beans with the sauce and let stand for at least 5 minutes.&nbsp; If you have time let marinate for 30 minutes.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Place green beans in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Cook 10-15 minutes on 400 F. Shake the basket every 5 minutes for even cooking. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '231.jpg', '231-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '00:32:37', 2, 0, 0, '', 899, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n114.119.137.125\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7412:356f:8bde:bf70', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b1ff620026130a211fc33a1715e2ac7caf4fb5aa', '2020-12-26 13:30:38', 0),
(232, 16, 'Paprika Suppe med Karbonadedeig', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Flott og sunn middag p&aring; en kj&oslash;lig kveld.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk grÃ¸nnsaker og hvitlÃ¸k.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>I en stekepanne stek karbonadedeigen. Etter noen minutter legg til sopp, paprika og lÃ¸k. Stek ferdig karbonadedeigen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ha alt over i en kasserolle og la det smÃ¥koke i 20 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server topped med ris eller blomkÃ¥l ris. Topp med gresk yoghurt, fersk koriander og revet ost.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '232.jpg', '232-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '05:06:23', 0, 0, 0, '0', 693, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7412:356f:8bde:bf70', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9ff45caab046fac4847567cb72e93098788e479d', '2020-12-26 13:32:06', 0),
(233, 16, 'Surs&oslash;t kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Vil du ha kinesisk takeaway, men samtidig v&aelig;re sunn? Pr&oslash;v denne surs&oslash;te kyllingen!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland sursÃ¸t saus ingredienser i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk grÃ¸nnsakerene,Â  ingefÃ¦r, hvitlÃ¸k, og kyllingen separat og sett til side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stek kylling i en panne til den er ferdig, ca 5 minutter. Hvis du bruker olje- eller non-stick spray, vÃ¦r oppmerksom pÃ¥ at nÃ¦ringsverdien endres nÃ¥r jeg lager maten i vann. Ta ut kyllingen og legg den pÃ¥ en tallerken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stek grÃ¸nnsakerene i en panne til de nÃ¥r en sprÃ¸ konsistens, ca 3-4 minutter. Legg til ingefÃ¦r og hvitlÃ¸k og stek i et minutt til.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>RÃ¸r denÂ sursÃ¸te sausen for Ã¥ sikre at maisstivelsen blandes godt. Legg sÃ¥usen og kyllingen i pannen. La det simre til sausen tykner, ca 1-2 minutter. Hvis sausen blir for tykk legg til litt vann, jeg bruker 30 ml ekstra per posjon.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med ris eller squash nudler! Du kan bruke hermetisert ananas, men juster ernÃ¦ringsinformasjonen da. Ta gjerne ut grÃ¸nnsakere du ikke liker. Andre erstatninger for grÃ¸nnsaker kan vÃ¦re aspargesbÃ¸nner eller vannkastanjer.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '233.jpg', '233-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '05:24:22', 2, 0, 0, '0', 639, '167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n2607:5300:120:36c::1\n173.212.247.190\n192.99.4.163', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:eda9:7d4:7a54:f056', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '53138c9cb943dc786006480fe8cdac492a4766ca', '2020-12-23 15:47:52', 0),
(234, 16, 'Hjemmelaget Taco', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Er du klar for Taco Fredag?', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â  Hakk lÃ¸k og hvitlÃ¸k.Â  Legg sopp i en matprosessor og bland til Ã¸nsket konsistens. Du kan ogsÃ¥ finhakke dem for hÃ¥nd.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland alle tÃ¸rre krydder i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brun karbonadedeig, mot slutten av koketiden, legg til lÃ¸k, hvitlÃ¸k og sopp.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â  Tilsett krydder, vann og tomatsaus og la dem smÃ¥koke i 10-15 minutter til sausen blir tykkere.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server over tortillas, pita brÃ¸d, <span dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"_3l3x\">taco-skjell </span></span> eller en grÃ¸nn salat. Jeg serverer min i mini Corn Tortillas. Topp hver taco med av gresk yoghurt, nyhakkede koriander og salat.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '234.jpg', '234-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '05:51:23', 14, 0, 0, '0', 805, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n185.191.171.23\n185.191.171.18\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n185.191.171.19', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '014e266c1d8f80969e5cd0157bee21ebb0ccfde6', '2020-12-26 13:33:46', 0),
(235, 16, 'Chili Laks', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En morsom og sunn vri p&aring; vanlige laks', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Forvarm ovnen til 200 grader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg aluminiumsfolie eller bakepapir i en stekesikker form eller pÃ¥ en stekeplate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â  Finhakk hvitlÃ¸k og chili. Bland sammen i en liten glassskÃ¥l med resten av krydderet.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg laksen i den tilberedte pannen og beleg med chili-saus.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake laksen i ovnen i 15-25 minutter, avhengig av filets tykkelse. Laksen er ferdig nÃ¥r den lett kan flakes med en gaffel.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med dampet brokkoli og ris.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '235.jpg', '235-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '05:57:47', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1090, '192.99.5.225\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n5.9.108.254\n204.12.226.26', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6d31a7a0ed107d4484c5afbc61470f8c2165c984', '2020-12-26 13:35:09', 0),
(236, 16, 'Squash og Sjampinjong Kylling Wok', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Inspirert av en tallerken p&aring; en Amerikansk resturant kjent som Panda Express', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk hvitlÃ¸k, sopp, squash og ingefÃ¦r. kut kylling i tynne stykker og dekk den med maisstivelse. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lag sausen ved Ã¥ kombinere sojasaus, sukker og riseddik i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Varm sesamolje i en panne over middels hÃ¸y varme. Tilsett kylling og stek til den er fedig, 3-5 minutter avhengig av tykkelsen pÃ¥ kyllingen din. Sette til side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg til squash, og sopp i pannen. La steke i 5 minutter. Tilsett hvitlÃ¸k og ingefÃ¦r og la steke i et minutt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg tilbake kyllingen og tilsett sausen. Kok til sausen tykner, ca 2-3 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server over ris eller blomkÃ¥l ris. Dryss over med sesamfrÃ¸.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '236.jpg', '236-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', '06:10:45', 2, 0, 0, '0', 969, '144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'ea08cfbab4e2375f30181882797514003dd0c862', '2020-12-26 05:12:01', 0),
(237, 90, 'Cucumber and Mint Salad', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious and refreshing salad', '<ul><li>\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\n<p>Cut the cucumber into thin slices, then divide it on the side so that it is cut into half-moons.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\n<p>Â  Cut red onions into thin slices. Finely chop mint. </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\n<p>Mix together vinegar, salt, pepper, mint in a small bowl. Then mix all ingredients together and serve. Can also be kept in the fridge for two-three days in an airtight container. </p>\n<p>Â </p>\n</li>\n</ul><p>If you are making this ahead of time, salt and drain the cucumbers either in a paper towel or in a colander for 20 minutes. This step is necessary for the cucumber to stay crunchy and not add excess water into the vinegar dressing. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/90/2019', '237.jpg', '237-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-08', '03:40:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1060, '112.113.68.216\n2a01:4f8:110:512d::2\n2a01:4f8:212:5da::2\n2a01:4f8:200:54aa::2\n89.163.242.108\n2a01:4f8:a0:410e::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:eda9:7d4:7a54:f056', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '760b943e65ffa85248efd3b16e32c813e6824e82', '2020-03-23 08:12:12', 0),
(238, 3, 'Tzatziki with Greek Yogurt', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Authentic Tzatziki often uses full-fat Greek yogurt and is usually topped with olive oil. This is a lightened up version using fat-free Greek yogurt.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate cucumber and crush garlic either with a presser or by hand. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine everything together in a bowl, add salt and pepper to taste. I use 0.12 teaspoon salt and 0.5 teaspoon pepper. Can be served right away but it tastes best if you let it rest in the fridge for a few hours first. Keep up to two days in an airtight container in the fridge. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with pita bread or vegetables. <br /><br />To make it less watery, sprinkle salt over your grated cucumber and wrap it in a paper towel to soak up excess cucumber juice. You can also deseed your cucumber.&nbsp; <br /><br />You can also add one teaspoon per serving of freshly chopped dill and 0.25 teaspoon of a grated lemon. For a more authentic flavor use full-fat Greek yogurt and 0.5 teaspoon olive oil per serving. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '238.jpg', '238-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-09', '06:53:19', 6, 0, 0, '', 1126, '185.191.171.6\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n5.9.108.254\n192.99.4.163', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '45845baff53aa7939e76d905405a223a51fd073f', '2020-12-27 01:49:51', 0),
(239, 3, 'Shrimp Taco', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Is it taco Tuesday yet? High in protein, low calories and tasty!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine spices and oil with shrimp, let marinate for 15 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a skillet over medium-high heat, add shrimp and cook until they are done, about 2-3 minutes on each side. Be careful to not overcook them as shrimp cook quickly. They will turn pink and form a loose C shape when they are done. If they start curling to tighter O shape they are overcooked.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in taco shells, tortillas, pita bread, or over a salad. Top with your favorite taco toppings, see the bottom of this recipe for ideas. In the photo, they are topped with a <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=9&amp;l=en\">Quick Coleslaw Mix</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=59&amp;l=en\">Cilantro Lime Yogurt.</a> Click on the names for the recipes. <br /><br /><br />You can use frozen shrimp, just let them defrost in the fridge completely beforehand and pat dry with a paper towel before marinating them.&nbsp;<br /><br />Taco Topping Ideas<br />- Fresh chopped cilantro <br />- Greek yogurt or sour cream<br />- Shredded Mexican cheese or <a href=\"../food/view_food.php?food_id=192&amp;l=en\"><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Queso </span><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Fresco </span>Mexican cheese.</a>&nbsp;<br />- Avocado or Guacamole<br />- Green onions<br />- Sliced Jalapeno<br />- Salsa or pico de gallo<br />- Corn</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '239.jpg', '239-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-09', '21:56:24', 0, 0, 0, '', 1169, '192.99.9.25\n192.99.5.225\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.34\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:1ccf:2f94:7278:4f14', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bd3b2c9a3a6930abc1813be3e4c7f2b05c259df7', '2020-12-26 18:52:35', 0),
(240, 3, 'Mexican Stew', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'When I was growing up I had this stew once a week. Sometimes from a spice mix known Norway&#039;s best-selling stew. Every now and then my mom would make it from scratch. I hope you enjoy her recipe!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop bell pepper, onions, and mince the garlic. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a pot or frying pan, add the ground beef and cook over medium heat. After a few minutes add the onions. Add the bell pepper towards the end of the ground beefs cook time.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>In a saucepan</strong><br />Add all the ingredients into a small pot.<br />Bring to a boil and let simmer for 10 minutes.<br /><br /><strong>In a slow cooker</strong><br />Add all the ingredients into a 2-quart slow cooker and mix.<br />Cook on high for 3-4 hours or on low for 6-7 hours.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over steamed rice or cauliflower rice and toasted sourdough. Top with greek yogurt, fresh parsley, corn, and shredded cheddar.<br /><br />For a thinner soup, add more stock. You can lower the amount of ground beef by substituting some with finely chopped mushroom. Can also be made with other meats such as shredded chicken, ground turkey, or ground chicken. &nbsp; </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '240.jpg', '240-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-10', '22:38:56', 14, 0, 0, '', 933, '60.180.123.198\n2a01:4f8:210:200b::2\n2a01:4f8:192:734b::2\n2a01:4f8:202:338a::2\n2a01:e0a:2c2:8e80:65ee:5755:298f:5af5\n2a01:4f8:201:126f::2\n192.99.6.138\n192.99.37.138\n192.99.10.170', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:8869:a514:ed04:f755', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '99141440786611ff8b6a576c877505d7a670b7d1', '2020-03-24 23:30:51', 0),
(241, 3, 'Chick-fil-A Grilled Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The secret behind the tasty chicken at Chik-fil-A is a good brine and a thin chicken breast that allows the chicken breast to cook evenly.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all ingredients in a bowl and let brine for 15-30 minutes. You can cover and put it in the fridge or leave it out to gain a lukewarm temperature that is ready for the grill/pan. After 15-30 minutes drain the liquid, let the chicken breast rest on a paper towel or in a colander for a minute or two.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a Market Salad<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=242&amp;l=en\"> (click for recipe)</a> or in a toasted whole wheat bun with lettuce, tomato, and cheese. <br /><br />Only 10% of the calories in the brine will be absorbed into the chicken breast so do not fear the teaspoon brown sugar or orange juice. <br /><br />Ingredients in Chik-fil-A\'s chicken breast, the ones in bold are the one&nbsp; in my recipe as well:<br />Seasoning [<strong>apple cider vinegar</strong>, soybean oil, yeast extract, <strong>salt</strong>, modified corn starch, palm oil, <strong>dehydrated garlic, dehydrated onion,</strong> corn maltodextrin, sea salt, natural flavor,<strong> sugar,</strong> <strong>chicken stock</strong>, cane molasses, chicken fat, <strong>spice,</strong> natural flavor {including smoke}, dextrose, <strong>lemon peel</strong>, citric acid, red bell pepper, <strong>orange juice concentrate</strong>, grape juice concentrate, natural flavor, <strong>paprika</strong>, <strong>vinegar</strong>, xanthan gum, ascorbic acid,]<br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '241.jpg', '241-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-11', '22:57:58', 0, 0, 0, '', 1057, '144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n185.191.171.45\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n185.191.171.16\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96', 0, '142.129.116.49', '', '841b32666109cbeffc5180ed5235fc0d7318d6d4', '2020-12-26 05:13:14', 0);
