(242, 3, 'Market Salad by Chick-fil-A', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'This and the cool wrap is my favorite dish at Chik-fil-A. Unfortunately, it cost over 9 dollars so I will make my own!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut up the vegetables and fruit, mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with grilled <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=241&amp;l=en\">Chik-fil-A\'s grilled chicken breast (click for recipe)</a> and granola, cranberries, pecans, almonds, walnuts, roasted almonds, glazed pecans, and blue cheese. <br /><br />Chik-fil-A\'s ingredients for Market Salad: <br /><strong>Romaine lettuce</strong>, chicken, <strong>red and green</strong> <strong>apple, strawberries</strong>, Granola glycerated cranberries, pecans, almonds, walnuts, green <strong>cabbage</strong>, <strong>blueberries</strong>, roasted almonds, glazed pecans, blue cheese, <strong>red leaf lettuce</strong>, green leaf lettuce.<br /><br />If you are making this recipe ahead of time I suggest reading SeriousEats article on how to prevent your apples from browning here: <a href=\"https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning.html\">https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning.html</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '242.jpg', '242-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-12', '01:01:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 959, '161.97.136.234\n167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n185.191.171.19\n95.91.110.121', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9cd52ba93d86a8c1cb1fcea5b3081a56b376248f', '2020-12-27 06:38:51', 0),
(243, 3, 'Tartar Sauce with Greek Yogurt', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to substitute some of the yogurts with mayo. You can also add finely chopped capers and as herbs like dill and parsley.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop onion and pickles. Mix everything together and let stand in the fridge for one hour before serving. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Because this is made without mayo I\'d recommend using a higher fat Greek yogurt, but the non-fat one works as well.&nbsp; In addition, you might want to add sweeteners such as a small amount of honey or Splenda. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '243.jpg', '243-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', '05:12:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1064, '144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n185.191.171.42\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96\n5.9.108.254', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd4e:229f:fd28:65ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c7f1395293b0db1247af05fe9f2db0f9d27c0bd0', '2020-12-26 05:14:14', 0),
(244, 3, 'Lean Fish for Fish &amp; Chips', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'No breadcrumbs or flour needed in this recipe. A skinny version of your regular fish &amp; chips but still tasty. I&#039;d recommend using cod or haddock.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Separate egg yolk and the egg white in a glass bowl.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices with the egg yolk to form a paste, you can substitute parsley and marjoram for tarragon or omit them. Whip egg white by itself with an electric mixer until white peaks forms, about 5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Carefully fold the egg yolk paste into the egg white. Dip each cod fillet in the egg mixture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pan<br />Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Spray lightly with non-stick spray and cook five minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.<br /><br />Oven<br />Place cod with the side the skin was on down on an oven-safe dish. Bake in a preheated oven at 400 F for 15-20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Do not count the entire batter in your calorie content, only count half towards the total nutrition. It makes about 46-gram batter, only 22 grams is used to coat 8 oz fillets. So each 4 oz fillet has an extra 15 calories from the batter, so the total calories are then 108. <br /><br />Serve with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=205\">Jicama Fries</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=243&amp;l=en\">Tartar Sauce</a> (click on names for recipes).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the recipe\'s photo, it has been pan-fried.&nbsp; This photo displays how it looks like after being baked in the oven: <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190413053950.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"584\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '244.jpg', '244-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', '05:28:39', 1, 0, 0, '', 1220, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n95.91.76.137\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd4e:229f:fd28:65ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '46495d113c7ccffbaaa1be970a770c200ffe90fd', '2020-12-27 04:21:13', 0),
(245, 3, 'Green Beans &amp; Chicken Stir-Fry', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I love this dish at Panda Express, but I don&#039;t like all the preservatives so now I make it at home. This dish has double the protein for the same amount of calories than the one at Panda Express, so enjoy with a good conscience!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop ends of green beans and onion into squares or wedges. Mince garlic and ginger. Chop chicken into bite size pieces, I like to do mine into thin strips or squares.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix sauce ingredients into a small bowl set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken in cornstarch and sesame oil. Pan fry over medium-high heat until it is done, about 5 minutes. Set aside on a plate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add green beans and onions into the pan and cook until crunchy, 4-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken and sauce. Cook, until heated throughout and the sauce, has thickened.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with rice and steamed veggies. If you do not have rice wine you can substitute it for soy sauce, but be aware that the dish becomes saltier then as rice wine has a sweeter flavor. I\'d definitely recommend purchasing rice wine for a flavor more similar to Panda Express.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '245.jpg', '245-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', '23:59:59', 2, 0, 0, '', 922, '185.191.171.3\n114.119.151.208\n185.191.171.20\n185.191.171.19\n185.191.171.18\n185.191.171.25\n2607:5300:60:3e58::1\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n167.114.158.215', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '8e6551028616ae23b1d46336f7732e8cb15a1163', '2020-12-27 08:50:38', 0),
(246, 3, 'Egg White Crepes', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Inspired by Crepini&#039;s Egg White Thins! These crepes are very universal. Make them sweet with berries and Greek yogurt or savory with lunch meat and mustard.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whisk together the egg whites, applesauce, flour, milk, and xanthan gum until smooth.&nbsp; If you do not have xanthan gum you can omit this, it just helps to combine the ingredients.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick cooking spray and set over low heat. I use an 8\" skillet. Pour a 1/4th cup of the batter into the skillet and spread the batter out with a tilting motion. Cook until the crepe starts to form bubbles on the top and is solid. Flip and cook another 2 minutes. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with Greek yogurt mixed with vanilla extract and berries. Or make it savory by using lunch meat, salad, and mustard.<br /><br />The two on the right are filled with Greek yogurt and cocoa. The three on the left with Greek yogurt and berries. <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190417125715.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"488\" /><br /><br />To store, let crepes cool and place in an airtight container or in a zip lock bag the fridge for 3-4 days. For best consistency place paper towels or parchment paper between each crepe. Can be frozen but thaw in the fridge.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '246.jpg', '246-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '01:33:06', 0, 0, 0, '', 2788, '161.97.136.234\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n95.91.110.121\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9eb52b5fa337e797a461353181632ca776e78bad', '2020-12-27 06:38:58', 0),
(247, 16, 'Dijon Laks', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Dijon sennep er en fin m&aring;te &aring; legge til den ekstra smaken i mat uten overfl&oslash;dig kalorier. Det fungerer spesielt godt over ovnbakt laks!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Forvarm ovnen til 200 C grader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â  Legg aluminiumsfolie eller bakepapir i en stekesikker form eller pÃ¥ en stekeplate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kutt lÃ¸k og hvitlÃ¸k i smÃ¥ terninger. Bland hvitlÃ¸k, sennep og krydder sammen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Â Plasser laks i formen med skinnsiden ned. Topp med sennepsausen, topp med lÃ¸k.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bak i ovnen i 20 minutter, eller til laks er ferdig. Den er ferdig nÃ¥r den enkelt kan flakes med en gaffel.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med ris og en side av grÃ¸nne grÃ¸nnsaker.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '247.jpg', '247-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '05:39:27', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1064, '161.97.136.234\n192.99.5.225\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n2a01:4f8:161:8046::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c8bf7d3580b5c836aaae04ebc116f6a09c73038d', '2020-12-27 06:39:08', 0),
(248, 16, 'Gr&oslash;nne B&oslash;nner og Kylling Wok', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Inspirert av en tallerken p&aring; en Amerikansk resturant kjent som Panda Express', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk ender av grÃ¸nne bÃ¸nner og lÃ¸k i firkanter. Hakkel hvitlÃ¸k og ingefÃ¦r. Hakk kylling i bite stÃ¸rrelse stykker, jeg liker Ã¥ gjÃ¸re min til tynne strimler eller firkanter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland saus ingredienser i en liten bolle satt til side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dekk kylling i majsstivelse og sesamolje. Stek pan over middels hÃ¸y varme til den er ferdig, ca 5 minutter. Sett til side pÃ¥ en tallerken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Legg grÃ¸nne bÃ¸nner og lÃ¸k i pannen og stek til knasende, 4-5 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett kylling og saus. Kok, til det er oppvarmet hele og sausen, har blitt tykkere.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med ris og dampet veggies. Hvis du ikke har risvin kan du erstatte det for Soyasaus/Sake / TÃ¸rr sherry / Eple juice. Hvis du bruker soyasaus sÃ¥ vÃ¦r klar over at retten blir saltere da risvin har en sÃ¸tere smak. Jeg vil absolutt anbefale Ã¥ kjÃ¸pe risvin for en smak som ligner pÃ¥ Panda Express.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '248.jpg', '248-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '05:55:30', 2, 0, 0, '0', 786, '2a01:4f8:210:200b::2\n2a01:4f8:202:338a::2\n2a01:e0a:2c2:8e80:65ee:5755:298f:5af5\n2a01:4f8:200:6406::2\n2a01:4f8:201:126f::2\n192.99.6.138', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '864117029c624bc3a39d87675ef223dbe8845a52', '2020-03-04 14:56:37', 0),
(249, 16, 'Stekt Torsk med Chili', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En deilig og rask m&aring;te &aring; lage tilapia p&aring;! V&aelig;r oppmerksom p&aring; at chilipulver er forskjellig fra cayennepepper. Bruk gjerne annen fisk som sei.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kombiner chilipulver, hvitlÃ¸kspulver (eller hakket hvitlÃ¸k) og salt i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gni fisken med krydderblandingen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett olje i en panne over middels hÃ¸y varme. Legg til fisken og stek til ferdig, vend en gang, ca. 4-7 minutter, avhengig av tykkelsen pÃ¥ filetene. Fisken er ferdig dersom den flaker nÃ¥r du trykker den lett med en gaffel.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med lime, grÃ¸nn salat, ris og asparges eller grÃ¸nne bÃ¸nner.</p>\r\n<p>NÃ¥r du steker fisk, er det tilrÃ¥delig Ã¥ holde det ut av kjÃ¸leskapet i 10-15 minutter, slik at temperaturen i pannen ikke endres nÃ¥r den tilberedes. OgsÃ¥ stek fisken med siden ikke hadde skinn pÃ¥ fÃ¸rst.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '249.jpg', '249-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '06:14:35', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1048, '192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n2a01:4f8:161:8046::2\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96\n5.9.108.254\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f8:200:814b::2\n2a01:4f8:191:2094::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'cebd475780eabe79546377ca74671bbb14f3a9b3', '2020-12-26 13:42:39', 0),
(250, 16, 'Chick-fil-A Grillet kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Hemmeligheten bak den velsmakende kyllingen ved Chik-fil-A er en god saltlake og et tynt kyllingbryst som gj&oslash;r at kyllingbrystet kan tilberedes jevnt.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hvis du ikke har et tynt kyllingbryst, sommerfugl det og slÃ¥ det flatt. Dette trinnet er nÃ¸dvendig fordi kyllingbrystet har en ujevn form, det vil ikke komme i kontakt med pannen eller grillen for Ã¥ steke jevnt som for eksempel biff gjÃ¸r.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kombiner alle ingrediensene i en bolle og ha i kyllingen, la stÃ¥ i 15-30 minutter. Du kan dekke og sette det i kjÃ¸leskapet eller la det vÃ¦re pÃ¥ benken for Ã¥ fÃ¥ en lunken temperatur som er klar for grillen / pannen. Etter 15-30 minutter drenerer vÃ¦sken, la kyllingbrystet hvile pÃ¥ et papirhÃ¥ndkle eller i en kolander i et minutt eller to.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray en stekepanne med non-stick spray eller bruk en grillpanne. Grill eller stek kylling 6-8 minutter avhengig av tykkelsen pÃ¥ kyllingbrystet eller inntil den indre temperaturen pÃ¥ kyllingen nÃ¥r 73 C. La kylling stÃ¥ 5-10 minutter fÃ¸r du kutter det opp.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=251&l=no\">Market Sala</a>t (klikk for oppskrift) eller pÃ¥ et ristetÂ  grovt hamburgerbrÃ¸d med salat, tomat og ost.<br /><br />Bare 10% av kaloriene i saltlake vil bli absorbert i kyllingbrystet, sÃ¥ frykt ikke teskelen brunt sukker eller appelsinjuice.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '250.jpg', '250-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '06:25:13', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1071, '127.0.0.1\n192.99.5.225\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n2a01:4f8:161:8046::2\n207.180.224.141', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '426085e4a9c36c3720feeaa3c991cac950615dff', '2020-12-31 11:10:08', 0),
(251, 16, 'Market Salat ala Chik-fil-A', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Dette er min favorittrett hos Chik-fil-A. Pr&oslash;v denne til middag i dag, du vil ikke angre!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Krutt opp grÃ¸nnsaker og frukt, bland.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=250&l=no\">grillet Chik-fil-A grillet kyllingbryst (klikk for oppskrift)</a>, granola, tranebÃ¦r, pekannÃ¸tter, mandler, valnÃ¸tter, stekt mandler og blÃ¥ost.<br /><br />Hvis du lager denne oppskriften pÃ¥ forhÃ¥nd, foreslÃ¥r jeg at du leser SeriousEats artikkel om hvordan du kan forhindre at eplene dine brenner her: https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning. html</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '251.jpg', '251-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '06:39:30', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1061, '127.0.0.1\n167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n2a01:4f8:161:8046::2\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'efe516f2614f62e08c6e5fe5f8cc1f402102cbf3', '2020-12-31 11:09:56', 0),
(252, 16, 'Kylling og Rotgr&oslash;nnsaker Suppe', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Lett og sunt! Du er velkommen til &aring; erstatte med gr&oslash;nnsaker som ristet k&aring;l, brokkoli, gr&oslash;nne b&oslash;nner, mais eller hva som helst annet er i kj&oslash;leskapet ditt.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk grÃ¸nnsakene til Ã¸nsket fasong og kyllingen i mindre biter. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>PÃ¥ stekeplate</strong><br />Tilsett ingredienser til en suppepanne. La det smÃ¥kokeÂ  i 15-20 minutter. Fjern lÃ¸vbladet og server.<br /><br /><strong>I slow cooker</strong><br />Plasser alle ingrediensene i en slow cooker/crockpot og rÃ¸r for Ã¥ blande. Dekk og kok pÃ¥ hÃ¸y i 3-4 timer eller pÃ¥ lav i 6-7 timer.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server toppet med ferske hakkede urter som koriander og vÃ¥rlÃ¸k. Ha gjerne til nyristet brÃ¸d. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '252.jpg', '252-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '07:00:03', 0, 0, 0, '0', 949, '5.9.108.254\n192.99.4.163\n2a01:4f8:200:814b::2\n2a01:4f8:191:2094::2\n144.76.14.153\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:4449::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'e10fb8133fa4a8bd9015202a53b062d432f8792a', '2020-12-22 10:16:59', 0),
(253, 3, 'Giant Berry Smoothie Bowl', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Rolled oats in your smoothie bowl keep you fuller longer than traditional smoothie bowls based on fruits. This is because oats have fiber that helps keep your blood sugar stable and are a low GI index food. Pick any frozen berry such as blueberries, cherries, raspberries, blackberries, or a mix! You can replace bananas with equal amounts of Greek yogurt.', '<p>There are three ways of making this smoothie bowl. I\'d recommend the cooked overnight version because it yields a greater volume and is affected by the resistant starch heating/cooling cycle.&nbsp; You can substitute banana with Greek yogurt or both.&nbsp; Also, I make my oats with water but you can use unsweetened almond milk or other kinds of milk. <br /><br /><br /><strong>Overnight, recommended!</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step 1<br /></strong><br />Combine oats and 300-gram water per serving in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish.<br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 2<br /></strong><br />Cover and place in the fridge. Freeze blueberries and banana.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 3<br /></strong><br />In the morning or 6 hours later, add everything to a blender and blend until desired consistency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Overnight, cold.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step 1<br /></strong><br />Combine oats and 200-gram water per serving in a bowl. Cover and place in fridge overnight or 8 hours.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 2<br /></strong><br />Freeze blueberries and banana.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 3<br /></strong><br />In the morning or 8 hours later, combine everything in a blender and blend until desired consistency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Right now, more gritty consistency.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Combine everything in a blender using 160-gram water per serving in your blender. Blend until desired consistency.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as walnuts, banana, peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.</p>\r\n<p>I recommend adding a dash salt to your rolled oats. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /><br />Made with blueberries and Greek yogurt instead of bananas:<br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190417125301.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"847\" height=\"635\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190417125358.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"950\" height=\"774\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '253.jpg', '253-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', '17:43:10', 0, 0, 0, '', 2148, '167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n114.119.137.125\n207.180.224.141\n185.191.171.26\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n5.9.108.254', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7cdc:d45f:27a:f684', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'aa9a58df335bf2ca6674b0d25c195d9f134b6300', '2020-12-27 04:23:23', 0),
(254, 3, 'Cauliflower Taco', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Looking for a great recipe for Meat Free Monday? Try Cauliflower Tacos!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Cut the cauliflower into desired shape. I usually do smaller florets or slices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop or puree the Chipotle Pepper In Adobo Sauce in a food processor.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add everything except the cauliflower into a bowl and mix. Add the cauliflower and toss with a Kitchen Tongs. You can also place them into a container and shake it, baby!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil-covered baking sheet. Bake in the oven 18-20 minutes until the cauliflower have a nice brown color.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in taco shells or mini tortillas. Top with your favorite taco toppings, I top mine with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=9&amp;l=en\">Quick Coleslaw Mix</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=59&amp;l=en\">Cilantro Lime Yogurt.</a> Click on the names for the recipes.&nbsp;<br /><br />Taco Topping Ideas<br />- Fresh chopped cilantro <br />- Greek yogurt or sour cream<br />- Shredded Mexican cheese or <a href=\"../food/view_food.php?food_id=192&amp;l=en\"><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Queso </span><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Fresco </span>Mexican cheese.</a>&nbsp;<br />- Avocado or Guacamole<br />- Green onions<br />- Sliced Jalapeno<br />- Salsa or pico de gallo<br />- Corn<br />- Sliced red cabbage</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '254.jpg', '254-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-15', '23:29:41', 26, 0, 0, '', 1609, '167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f42d:b52a:c688:4fa', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '324d0517ae78e8a27debc840964708ff3cdbdfc1', '2020-12-27 04:23:49', 0),
(255, 3, 'Salt &amp; Vinegar Cauliflower', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that loves salt and vinegar potato chips? This low-calorie dish mimics that flavor very well!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cauliflower into the desired size and add to a bowl. Pour over the vinegar, oil, and salt. Toss to mix. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil covered baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until they start to brown. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with chopped fresh parsley.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '255.jpg', '255-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-18', '04:30:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1191, '167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n114.119.138.25\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.158.241\n167.114.159.99\n5.9.108.254', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '8883fdbe648fd8cfcc4e837b8a3bff8fbfbc7e57', '2020-12-27 04:24:21', 0),
(256, 3, 'Chipotle Tofu Sliders for Sandwiches', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and easy to make!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how to follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice tofu into thin slices, either lengthwise or crosswise.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients except tofu into a small bowl. Cover tofu slices with the mixture and place in the fridge to marinate for 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Bake tofu slices in the oven on a parchment covered cookie sheet for 20-30 minutes, flipping once.<br /><br /><strong>Pan-fried</strong><br />Heat up a skillet over medium-high and coat with non-stick spray.&nbsp; Cook tofu slices for 5 minutes on each side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve on a sandwich bread topped with your favorite toppings. Such as lettuce, spinach, tomatoes, bell peppers, cucumbers, avocado, onions, sprouts, a Greek yogurt sauce such as <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=5&amp;l=en\">Thousand Island</a> or <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=38&amp;l=en\">Chipotle Sauce</a>.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '256.jpg', '256-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-18', '22:39:31', 25, 0, 0, '', 1384, '167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n114.119.132.43\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a9d0:7d61:58fb:d493', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '86c6dac75d86f95203b54b893f6591ab29b67e44', '2020-12-27 04:26:09', 0),
(257, 3, 'Spicy Glazed Tofu', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The chili sauce gives a spicy flavor and the sweetness from hoisin sauce balances out the spice in this perfect combination.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how to follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice tofu into thin slices, either lengthwise or crosswise.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients except tofu into a small bowl. Cover tofu slices with the mixture and place in the fridge to marinate for 30 minutes or an hour if you have the time.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven Baked</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Bake tofu slices in the oven on a parchment covered cookie sheet for 20-30 minutes, flipping once.<br /><br /><strong>Pan-fried</strong><br />Heat up a skillet over medium-high and coat with non-stick spray or sesame oil.&nbsp; Cook tofu slices for 5 minutes on each side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in a salad, as a main entree, or in sandwiches.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Differences between pan-fried and oven baked</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190419111353.jpg\" /></p>\r\n<p>Great for sandwiches too!</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190419111912.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" /></p>\r\n<p>Or in a salad topped with your favorite dressing</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190419111924.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '257.jpg', '257-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-19', '23:06:13', 26, 0, 0, '', 1501, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.38\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '3f1a2ce7c2c4ad6e1711f90c02b92253055843e2', '2020-12-27 04:27:02', 0),
(258, 3, 'Easy Shrimp &amp; Vegetables Sheet Pan', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to switch or add more vegetables such as mushrooms, green beans, asparagus. You can also use lemon pepper instead of regular black pepper.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 400 F. Mix spice mix in a small bowl, set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop veggies into the desired shape and mix with half the spice mix.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat shrimp with the remaining spice mix and set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil. Line the sheet pan with veggies and place in the oven for 10-15 minutes, until vegetable brown. Add shrimp and cook an additional 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Goes well topped with freshly grated carrots. Serve with a salad or rice.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '258.jpg', '258-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-22', '01:51:33', 0, 0, 0, '', 1070, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n185.191.171.25\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n144.76.60.198\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n5.9.108.254', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:310d:71c7:863:1eed', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '971b910c82487c4effa2a4818b7fcbe7882d431f', '2020-12-27 04:27:30', 0),
(259, 3, 'Banana muffins', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Inspired by my banana bread recipe. Made using my mom&#039;s muffin technique for extra fluffy muffins.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Place muffin liners into a muffin pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mash one banana and mix it with all the wet ingredients.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients into a bowl, I like to sift them through a colander to make sure there are no lumps. Mix and make a hole in the middle. Pour the wet ingredients into this hole and fold in the dry ingredients, do not overmix. It is ok that there is some lumps are the batter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Scoop batter into muffin liners, I use a tablespoon to make this easier. For each muffin liner, I use about 48 gram of the batter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake in the preheated oven for 7-8 minutes. Turn the heat down to 375 and bake until finished, around 7-9 more minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '259.jpg', '259-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-22', '02:01:07', 23, 0, 0, '', 1891, '114.119.138.199\n167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n185.191.171.43\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:310d:71c7:863:1eed', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'ebd21892797e6d62eb6e252a3e27142cd0390b58', '2020-12-27 09:22:52', 0),
(261, 3, 'Pasta &amp; Seasonal Roasted Vegetables', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'An easy and tasty dinner that you can customize with leftovers from the fridge. Feel free to add a source of protein such as Spicy Glazed Tofu or Chipotle Chicken.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop bell pepper, onion, and zucchini and place on the sheet pan. Lightly salt them. If desired, coat with oil. Let bake for 10-20 minutes until they are browned.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Boil pasta after directions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop and combine tomato, garlic, basil with red wine vinegar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix pasta, veggies with the tomato, garlic and basil sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with red pepper flakes, parmesan cheese, and freshly chopped carrots.<br /><br />You can also use balsamic vinegar.2-gram basil = 1 tablespoon.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '261.jpg', '261-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-22', '16:01:32', 0, 0, 0, '', 677, '185.191.171.4\n185.191.171.2\n185.191.171.43\n167.114.116.25\n185.191.171.23\n185.191.171.39\n173.249.2.13\n185.191.171.22\n185.191.171.34\n2a01:4f8:150:2370::2\n95.91.76.136', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:213d:6f50:1a3b:40b', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0d1f182c06cf2d04809bd517b25139ef3d67fef0', '2020-12-26 00:42:28', 0),
(262, 3, '3 Ingredient Protein Cookies', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Tired of your regular protein shake? Mix it up with these simple protein cookies. See the bottom of this recipe for different variations such as with an egg or egg white.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper or use a silicone baking mat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine ingredients, make sure to use&nbsp; fresh baking powder. Spread each cookie out on the baking tray using a full teaspoon of batter for each.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake in oven 8-10 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Let cool before eating for a crispier cookie. <span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">I used Optimum Nutrition Vanilla Whey in my cookies but other protein powders will also work. If you use an unflavored protein powder, add a teaspoon vanilla extract and sweeten to taste. </span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190424011607.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"977\" /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190424011618.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"675\" /><br /><br /><br /><strong>Variation of this recipe using egg whites and whole egg:</strong></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Replace apple sauce with egg white</strong><br />The batter is sticky and hard to spread on the cookie tray. Made dry, rubber texture cookies. <br />Nutritional breakdown: 137 calories, 28-gram protein, 1-gram fat, 3-gram carbs. <br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Apple sauce (20 gram) and egg white</strong><br />This created a bread consistency, it was moist and reminded me of a sponge cake. Makes a bigger serving of batter that yields about 15 cookies. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 147 calories, 28-gram protein, 1-gram fat, 5-gram carbs. Picture 4. </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Replace applesauce with a whole large egg<br /></strong> The batter is sticky. However, the thinner cookies were completely crunchy.&nbsp; Thicker ones were crunchier than other recipes. Probably my favorite flavor and texture wise. Created 16 cookies. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 192 calories, 30-gram protein, 6-gram fat, 3-gram carbs. Picture 3.<br /></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Apple sauce (10 gram) and whole large egg</strong><br />This was the moistest cookies and with a mild sweet flavor. Makes a lot more cookies than the other recipes, about 19 of them. Picture 2. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 197 calories, 28-gram protein, 6-gram fat, 5-gram carbs. </span></span><br /></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>1. Original recipe. 2. Whole egg with applesauce. <br /></strong></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>3. Replace applesauce with a whole egg. 4. Egg white with applesauce.</strong> <br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190426094009.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"900\" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '262.jpg', '262-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-23', '02:11:48', 0, 0, 0, '', 3082, '185.191.171.36\n114.119.136.113\n185.191.171.1\n185.191.171.38\n185.191.171.35\n185.191.171.7\n185.191.171.6', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9b46f97d7bd4b83577329a4aa704234dfb8ed97c', '2020-12-27 00:18:11', 0),
(263, 3, 'Egg White Oatmeal: Never Ending Edition', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Ever wanted a GIANT bowl of something? Try this never-ending oatmeal!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make your oatmeal as you normally would. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">Click for a recipe that adds even more volume to your regular oatmeal.</a> </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add two egg-whites to a glass or stainless steel bowl. M<span data-offset-key=\"979i1-0-0\">ix with an electronic mixer until it forms white stiff peaks. Start with the mixer on slow, when bubbles form you can increase the speed. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gently fold egg-whites into your oatmeal. Cook in microwave or stovetop until egg-whites are fully cooked, about. 2-4 minutes. Stir every 30-60 seconds to make sure that egg-white cooks evenly. Careful that you do not overcook the eggs as they have a tendency to become rubber consistency then. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite oatmeal toppings. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '263.jpg', '263-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-24', '00:34:07', 0, 0, 0, '', 1034, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n114.119.138.199\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n185.191.171.45', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'dee776be907de90b301318ea6265a652737f779b', '2020-12-27 04:28:54', 0),
(264, 3, 'Sriracha Dressing', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'The all-time favorite hot sauce is taken to another level in this Greek Yogurt Dressing.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all the ingredients in a small bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you feel like the dressing is too thick add a teaspoon of water. <br />Can be stored in an airtight container for 2-3 days in the fridge.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '264.jpg', '264-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-24', '01:24:31', 0, 0, 0, '', 886, '114.119.138.199\n167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n185.191.171.35\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', '', '72c618bd9c6c07a01e97a1cd9ebb069803372231', '2020-12-27 06:34:34', 0),
(265, 3, 'Thin Pizza Crust Recipe', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that is tired of eating tortilla or pita pizzas... This crust is better than DiGiorno&#039;s ultra-thin pizza! Fits one 10&quot; round pizza pan. You can make it without yeast, look at the bottom of this recipe for directions.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Carefully measure out and add all ingredients to a bowl. Mix together using a spatula, once combined kneed the dough for 5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Let the dough rise covered in a plastic wrap for 30 minutes while the oven preheats to 425 F.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add a pinch of salt and roll out the dough into the desired shape using a rolling pin. It might take a bit of practice before you are able to roll it very thin, so be patient. Place on a parchment covered pizza pan or on a baking tray.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Top with your favorite pizza toppings and bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Since this is a thin pizza crust you don\'t want to overcrowd it with toppings. If you put too much the crust will become saggy. I recommend 28-gram / 1 oz cheese per serving. Also, brushing on the sauce helps make sure you don\'t put too much.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To make it easier to roll out the dough, use a parchment paper under your it and a plastic wrap over the dough:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190425021751.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"850\" height=\"704\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Make sure you roll it out thin enough so it wraps around your hand, this still needs to be rolled thinner:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190425021719.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></p>\r\n<p>Finished result:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190425021741.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"683\" /></p>\r\n<p>This pizza has:<br />One serving dough, 175 calories. <br />28 gram Kroger Cheese - Cheese Mexican Blend 2% Reduced Fat Cheese, 80 calories.<br />Pace Picante Sauce - Salsa, 30 ml, 10 calories.<br />Kroger - Ricotta Cheese Low Fat, 10 gram, 10 calories. <br />Scallion, 5 g, Peppers, jalapeno 5 g, bell pepper 5 gram, 1 gram cilantro, 5 calories. <br /><strong>Total 280 calories.</strong></p>\r\n<p>I recommend making your pizza dough with yeast. However, if you want you can make it without. Just replace yeast with 0.5 teaspoon baking powder per serving. The dough is a bit sticker and harder to work with, but not by a lot. This is the result of a yeast-free dough: </p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190425110226.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"762\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '265.jpg', '265-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-25', '01:50:11', 0, 0, 0, '', 1410, '185.191.171.13\n185.191.171.8\n185.191.171.12\n114.119.137.125\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n185.191.171.42\n185.191.171.24', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f169:6e23:516c:26c2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '3d37c862f48c8c12f5cf5fc862f6b501830566b6', '2020-12-26 19:25:09', 0),
(266, 3, 'Cheesecake Pancakes', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious pancakes made with ricotta for extra protein and cheesecake-like texture.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Zest a lemon.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another, except the blueberries. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Griddle</strong><br />Preheat a griddle to 375. Use a tablespoon to pour batter onto the griddle, sprinkle with blueberries on top of pancakes. Cook until bubbles on top of your pancake bursts, then flip and cook until done about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong>Skillet</strong><br />Place a skillet over medium heat, wait until hot before you add the batter. Use a tablespoon to pour the batter onto your skillet, sprinkle with blueberries on top of each pancake. Cook until bubbles on top of your pancake bursts, then flip and cook until done about 2 more minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Sprinkling the blueberries over pancakes helps avoid too many in one pancake and your batter from turning blue. I make 8, 4\" pancakes with this batter. Depending on your pan and/or griddle you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '266.jpg', '266-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-26', '01:15:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1294, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.21\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n185.191.171.18\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9547:d115:b5b3:4766', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'a8241fc9e00ab7592d18f6889341e100f54c9793', '2020-12-27 04:30:35', 0),
(267, 3, 'Spicy Glazed Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'This is the perfect sticky, spicy, and sweet chicken recipe while remaining low-calorie.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine sauce ingredients in a bowl and set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop chicken into bite-size pieces , I like mine in thin strips. Coat with cornstarch and a pinch of salt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place a skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until it is done, 3-5 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir sauce and add to the skillet. Cook until heated through and the sauce has thickened.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with rice, steamed veggies, or <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\">zoodles</a>. It is also wonderful cold in a salad:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190426021839.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '267.jpg', '267-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-26', '02:03:10', 2, 0, 0, '', 976, '167.114.64.97\n114.119.151.208\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n185.191.171.2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n144.91.125.96\n185.191.171.4', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:158a:29be:9848:7778', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '4d21ea491f642870ffe0d1eecafbc83528a146be', '2020-12-27 04:31:18', 0),
(268, 3, 'Ranch made with Greek Yogurt', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'I Can&#039;t Believe It&#039;s Not Ranch ;)', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all ingredients in a bowl. For best flavor let stand in fridge 15-30 minutes before serving. Add a tablespoon (15 ml)&nbsp; water per serving for a thinner consistency. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can replace 20-gram Greek yogurt with mayo for a more full-fat ranch consistency.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '268.jpg', '268-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-27', '01:30:21', 0, 0, 0, '', 728, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n5.9.108.254\n2a01:4f8:200:814b::2\n2a01:4f8:191:2094::2\n144.76.14.153', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'e81cd07f69703e6c27ba6ea3fbadb737665c41d9', '2020-12-27 04:31:44', 0),
(269, 3, 'Lemon Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and easy way to cook chicken', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Zest a lemon. Mix spices, zest, and lemon juice in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breast with the spice mix. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken it in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '269.jpg', '269-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-27', '01:40:02', 0, 0, 0, '', 750, '161.97.136.234\n185.191.171.20\n114.119.136.113\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n185.191.171.38\n144.76.60.198', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', '', 'b11f9326860d5e5d5fd67804b0f173450528de9a', '2020-12-27 06:39:27', 0);
")
