(270, 3, 'Daikon Radish Fries', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Daikon has 18 calories per 100-gram, making it the perfect diet food. Low-carb and delicious.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the daikon radish into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a large bowl mix together the spices and daikon radish. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the daikon radish with spices and oil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">Place Daikon strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30-45 minutes.&nbsp;<br /></span><br /><strong>Air-Fryer&nbsp;</strong><br />Place the daikon radish strips in a single layer in the air fryer basket and cook for 10 minutes on 350 F.&nbsp; Shake the basket halfway through. <span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook an additional 5 minutes on 375 F.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=268&amp;l=en\">ranch</a> and topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '270.jpg', '270-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-27', '01:46:45', 0, 0, 0, '', 1022, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n185.191.171.13\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n185.191.171.6', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'eb137d1b9161dd5e6508d27c636ea47fe212bc6f', '2020-12-27 04:32:22', 0),
(271, 3, 'Powdered Peanut Butter Cookies', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Makes 6 giant and 9 regular sized cookies.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper or use a silicone baking mat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine ingredients, make sure to use fresh baking powder. Depending on your powdered peanut butter you might have to use more or less water so add it in increments. Spread each cookie thin on the baking tray using a full teaspoon of batter for each.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake in oven 10-12 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When you take them out of the oven they will be soft so let cool before eating! You can use other sweeteners instead of the monk fruit blend I use.</p>\r\n<p>Different sugars will create different results, here I made them using splenda:<br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190429015827.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"694\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '271.jpg', '271-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-29', '01:43:24', 0, 0, 0, '', 3323, '185.191.171.43\n167.114.64.97\n114.119.136.113\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c1df:140c:be77:ce06', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2842d60630984355546776eda9e50c4d5ebfa270', '2020-12-27 08:18:33', 0),
(272, 3, 'Cilantro &amp; Lime Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'An easy and tasty way to make chicken, perfect for meal prep, salads or by itself.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cilantro. Mix Worchester sauce with lime. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breast with the lime mix, cilantro, salt, and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken it in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a> </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '272.jpg', '272-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-29', '02:02:31', 0, 0, 0, '', 739, '161.97.136.234\n167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n114.119.137.125\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2607:5300:60:3880::1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c1df:140c:be77:ce06', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f21b6bfe7be6ea87aa560e434c4066cb6ee6622c', '2020-12-27 06:39:50', 0),
(273, 3, 'Baked Tofu Burger', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to swap out veggies or add more spice.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how to follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.</a> Make sure that you drained all the water from the Tofu. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop onion, carrots, chipotle peppers, and bell pepper into small dices. Crumble the tofu into a bowl. Add the vegetables, cornstarch, salt, and pepper to taste. Combine everything.&nbsp; </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Form into two patties, I like to use a 4 oz patty maker for this. Set the patties in the fridge to chill for 30 minutes, it is not necessary but I feel it is easier to handle them after they been chilled. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat oven to 350 F. Have a parchment or wax paper on a cookie sheet and place patties on top. Bake 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite burger toppings. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '273.jpg', '273-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-30', '01:15:53', 26, 0, 0, '', 1192, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n185.191.171.5\n185.191.171.11\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n185.191.171.25\n167.114.159.99', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'ccb8b5d93a9137c45844a94c954976d6c1b6a88f', '2020-12-27 04:35:09', 0),
(274, 3, 'Easy Lime Tofu', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that loves to make dinner in the oven!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add soy sauce, lime juice, and sesame oil in a bowl and mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop tofu into desired bite-size pieces.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine tofu with the marinade and let marinate in the fridge for 30 minutes to an hour.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake on 400 F for 30-40 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a green salad, or with rice and vegetables.&nbsp; Goes great topped with freshly chopped cilantro.</p>\r\n<p>For the marinade, the tofu only absorbs about 1/3rd of the liquid. So only 1/3rd of the marinade towards the total calories. So each serving have 13 calories from the marinade. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '274.jpg', '274-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-30', '01:35:52', 26, 0, 0, '', 995, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n5.9.108.254', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2222920f44164ec60ebeb1a66e5d6826b640dd73', '2020-12-27 04:36:09', 0),
(275, 3, 'Pumpkin Muffins', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Makes 3 muffins so adjust the serving to how many you&#039;d like to make.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Place muffin liners into a muffin pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not overmix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into muffin liners using a spoon, I do about 50&nbsp; gram batter in each. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake for 23-30 minutes. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can switch whole pastry flour for all-purpose flour. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">You can also use another sweetener than Monkfruit with erythritol</span></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '275.jpg', '275-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-04-30', '01:44:48', 0, 0, 0, '', 1098, '185.191.171.38\n114.119.138.199\n144.91.125.96\n5.9.108.254\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f9:2a:bcc::2\n144.76.14.153\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2', 0, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '252f126de25e63ff478cc3b4fe86e155b1b30a95', '2020-12-26 16:51:21', 0),
(276, 3, 'Chipotle &amp; Lime Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Chipotle Shrimp is great in tortilla&#039;s, with rice, or over pasta for a healthy and tasty dinner.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop the chipotle pepper with adobo sauce. Add chipotle peppers, lime, and spices in a bowl. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Toss the shrimp in spice mix and let marinade for 30 minutes. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pan-fried:</strong> <br />Heat a skillet over medium-high heat, add shrimp and cook until they are done, about 2-3 minutes on each side. <br />Heat a large heavy-duty or cast iron skillet on high heat for 2 minutes. Remove shrimp from marinade. Add shrimp to pan; saut&eacute; 3 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. <br /><br /><strong>BBQ:</strong> <br />Preheat your grill to medium-high heat. Thread shrimp on skewers and grill them about 2 minutes per side. <br /><br /><strong>Oven:</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil.&nbsp; Add shrimp and cook in the preheated oven for about 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.</p>\r\n<em>Be careful to not overcook them as shrimp cook quickly. They will turn pink and form a loose C shape when they are done. If they start curling to tighter O shape they are overcooked.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with freshly chopped cilantro, crushed red pepper, and a squeeze of lime.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '276.jpg', '276-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-01', '01:36:47', 0, 0, 0, '', 678, '114.119.156.144\n144.91.125.96\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n2a01:4f8:190:4449::2\n192.99.7.182\n158.69.243.99\n2a01:4f8:190:342f::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n2607:5300:60:3880::1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:409f:21b4:4acf:abd2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '24189f9ce3731afeba44c05c9550655c01dcc17f', '2020-12-26 13:13:38', 0),
(277, 3, 'Pumpkin Pancakes', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious mousse-like consistency makes these pancakes one of my all time favorites!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><br /><span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Griddle</strong><br />Preheat a griddle to 375. Use a tablespoon to pour batter onto the griddle. Cook until pancakes start to change color to a deeper brown, then flip and cook until done about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong>Skillet</strong><br />Place a skillet over medium heat, wait until hot before you add the batter. Use a tablespoon to pour the batter onto your skillet.</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"> Cook until pancakes start to change color to a deeper brown, then flip and cook until done about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I make four and a half, 4\" pancakes with the batter. Depending on your pan and/or griddle you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '277.jpg', '277-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-03', '00:27:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 933, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n185.191.171.8\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96\n5.9.108.254\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f9:2a:bcc::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7595:3952:5154:db6f', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b442b4bbdef7da20d08e6225656483e7a8bac45f', '2020-12-27 04:36:33', 0),
(278, 3, 'Buffalo Cauliflower', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Hot &amp; Delicious Roasted Cauliflower', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Mix ketchup and hot sauce in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cauliflower into the desired size and add to a bowl. Pour over the hot sauce mix and toss to mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil covered baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until they start to brown.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '278.jpg', '278-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-03', '18:00:58', 0, 0, 0, '', 805, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n167.114.158.215\n207.180.224.141\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96\n5.9.108.254\n167.114.116.38\n2a01:4f9:2a:bcc::2\n144.76.14.153', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9d37:4227:c46d:839f', '', 'fc89eb9863c3b7bef0f3cee562271d355c5cf5ca', '2020-12-27 04:37:07', 0),
(279, 3, 'Chili Lime Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Easy and tasty chicken that is perfect for meal prep!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices and lime juice in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breasts with the spice mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken it in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '279.jpg', '279-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-03', '18:11:15', 0, 0, 0, '', 686, '161.97.136.234\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n95.91.110.121\n2607:5300:60:3880::1\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n185.191.171.22\n144.76.60.198\n144.76.186.38', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9d37:4227:c46d:839f', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b5981acb23ce11644390d32f6d893ca0c53e790b', '2020-12-27 06:39:55', 0),
(280, 3, 'Pumpkin Waffles', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Adding an egg white is optional however I recommend it as it make the waffles more crispy. Makes four 4&quot; waffles (same size as Eggo waffles) or 2 regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you are using egg white, whip it until stiff peaks form and set aside. <br />Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the eggwhite until mixed.&nbsp; <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\nCook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I make four and a half, 4\" waffles with each serving of the batter. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>\r\n<p>For crispier waffles, let sit a bit longer in the waffle maker after they are done or leave them in the oven on 225 degrees after they are done.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Here made without an egg white:<br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190503114229.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" /><br /><br /><strong>Topped with Pumpkin Froyo. Recipe at <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=282&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=282&amp;l=en</a></strong> <br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190503114314.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '280.jpg', '280-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-03', '22:11:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 992, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n167.114.158.215\n114.119.129.199\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n144.91.125.96', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:681e:fe6e:cc42:38ba', '', 'b444da6783beb27fe9c55139d4c8def9b99c9069', '2020-12-27 04:38:19', 0),
(281, 3, 'Carrot Fries', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'I love to use rainbow carrots for a stunning looking dish!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the carrots into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a large bowl mix together the spices and carrots. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the carrots with spices and oil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Place the carrot strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 15-20 minutes on 425 F, flip once. <br /><br /><strong>Air fryer</strong><br />Place the carrot strips in a single layer in the basket and cook for 10 minutes on 375 F. Shake the basket half way through. For a crispier result increase the air frier to 400 F during the last 5 minutes of the cook time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '281.jpg', '281-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-03', '22:33:00', 0, 0, 0, '', 859, '167.114.64.97\n114.119.132.146\n144.76.120.197\n95.91.76.137\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n5.9.108.254', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:681e:fe6e:cc42:38ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '493e9142e588ed80bd104742db582dc15dda970f', '2020-12-27 04:39:24', 0),
(282, 3, 'Pumpkin Frozen Yogurt', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Creamy and so tasty. Reminds me of Halo Top&#039;s pumpkin flavor!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>If using Guar Gum</strong>: Mix half the milk with Guar Gum using a hand mixer. Then add everything else and mix for a couple of minutes.<br /><br /><strong>If omitting Guar Gum</strong>:<br />Mix together the ingredients using a hand mixer on medium speed for a couple of minutes. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>If using Guar Gum</strong>: Leave in the fridge for an hour to allow Guar Gum to fully work. Then pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.<br /><br /><strong>If&nbsp; omitting Guar gum</strong>: <br />Pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can omit the Guar Gum &amp; Soy Lecithin but I find that it helps to keep the frozen yogurt softer and gives more volume.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you do not have an ice cream maker you can use one of these three options. It will not yield the same result but still delicious:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">Freeze the mixture until semi-frozen in \"blender friendly sizes\" and then use a blender to get the right consistency.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">Freeze the mixture in a container that you stir every 30 minutes for around 2 hours.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">You can also mold it into pop sticks or make Greek yogurt bark, see this recipe: <a class=\"s1w8oh2o-27 tTnje\" href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=169\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=169</a></li>\r\n</ol>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '282.jpg', '282-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-04', '16:27:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 737, '167.114.64.97\n144.76.120.197\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '654cb0ff06808a0784171880f71f649af0012aa4', '2020-12-27 04:39:59', 0),
(283, 3, 'Waffles', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'I use a mini waffle iron, but it makes enough batter for two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whip egg white until stiff peaks forms and set aside. <br />Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp; <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\nCook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I make five and a half, 4\" waffles. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>\r\n<p>For crispier waffles check out this recipe:&nbsp;<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en</a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Feel free to add 0.5 teaspoon cinnamon and/or a teaspoon vanilla extract.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '283.jpg', '283-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-04', '16:49:39', 0, 0, 0, '', 1134, '167.114.64.97\n114.119.137.125\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n185.191.171.11\n173.249.30.147', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', '', 'f2dbe3bddb236028f0a1f173bb863cde9e25552d', '2020-12-27 04:40:29', 0),
(284, 3, 'Microwave Chocolate Sauce', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Let cool before eating for a thicker sauce.', '<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix everything into a large microwave-safe bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Microwave for 2 minutes for a thinner consistency or 2 minutes and 30 seconds for a thicker consistency, stop to stir every 30 sec. Watch the sauce as it might turn into a brownie-like consistency if it is microwaved too long. If this happens, add a small amount of water and stir it back to liquid again.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir in vanilla extract.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Can be served warm but I prefer to let it cool for an hour in the fridge so it becomes thicker.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '284.jpg', '284-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-05', '00:32:47', 0, 0, 0, '', 951, '185.191.171.17\n185.191.171.23\n167.114.64.97\n114.119.138.199\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.42', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '508a470adf8cd16af5ecd2b97f097acdd007ed0a', '2020-12-27 05:47:59', 0),
(285, 3, 'Parsley and Lemon Precooked Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The perfect summer dish. No cooking involved when using precooked shrimp. Easy, quick, and tasty.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop fresh parsley. Mix with spices, lemon juice, and red wine vinegar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat precooked shrimp with marinade and let marinate in the fridge for at least 3 hours, up to 24 hours.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a green salad, as finger food, with cold pasta,&nbsp; rice, or with steamed vegetables.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '285.jpg', '285-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-05', '04:48:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 668, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.5\n144.76.120.197\n204.12.197.234\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fe753ac15b2f75fd0d443d7917caafde29568e8a', '2020-12-27 04:41:31', 0),
(286, 3, 'Jalapeno &amp; Tomato Dip', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'The perfect dip to raw veggies or tortilla chips', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place veggies in a food processor and pulse until finely chopped.&nbsp; You might want to drain the liquid in coriander if there is too much so your dip does not get too runny.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix greek yogurt, veggies, paprika, and a pinch of salt in a bowl. Let stand 30 minutes in the fridge before serving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '286.jpg', '286-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-05', '23:47:23', 0, 0, 0, '', 687, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.36\n144.76.120.197\n185.191.171.5\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n167.114.159.99\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:fca7:fd7a:cec7:d6', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '79d4d9f01d35c9bc8db2767d74d34ef857ca7521', '2020-12-27 04:42:00', 0),
(287, 3, 'Sparkling Iced Tea', 7, 'en', 'United States', 'Perfect summer drink', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brew tea and let chill.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix tea with equal parts of sparkling water or soda. Add sweetener to taste.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with fresh lime or lemon juice.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/7/3/2019', '287.jpg', '287-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-07', '22:58:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 767, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.23\n192.99.5.225\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n144.76.120.197\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7c3c:71e8:3b56:4b9', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'a241384499f932e1477849058c70ae053cc1205c', '2020-12-27 04:42:52', 0),
(288, 3, 'Protein Powder Mug Cake', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Add up to 10-grams cocoa powder for a deeper flavor. As written it has a mild cocoa flavor. Sweetener is not necessary but it can be added depending on how sweet you like your cake!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients into a cereal sized bowl or big mug, mix well.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add applesauce and milk, mix.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Microwave 2 minutes and 30 seconds stopping after 1-2 minutes to check if done.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with whipped cream, ice cream, or fresh berries.&nbsp;<br /><br />I used ON 100% Whey but other whey/casein based protein powders should also work.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/blog/en/5/3_190510012802.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '288.jpg', '288-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-07', '23:02:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 1235, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.5.225\n185.191.171.9\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n114.119.136.113\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n37.57.218.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '1be40b78a8cf905a3e4123cba03c964978e32be6', '2020-12-27 04:43:36', 0),
(289, 3, 'Jalapeno Dip', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'The regular cilantro gets a spicy twist with this dip!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Place garlic and jalapeno in a food processor and pulse until finely chopped.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Mix all the other ingredients into the food processor or a bowl. Let stand 30 minutes in the fridge before serving.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '289.jpg', '289-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-08', '23:30:37', 0, 0, 0, '', 572, '2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n173.212.247.190\n192.99.4.163\n2a01:4f9:2a:bcc::2\n173.208.130.202\n192.99.7.182\n2607:5300:60:3e58::1\n185.191.171.3', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:55ec:84e3:28c1:2730', '', '6a325c13b4eb74e34e54a3a48c0375a1d5af2afe', '2020-12-22 19:34:15', 0),
(290, 3, 'Cold Asian Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious way to flavor your precooked shrimp.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cilantro and scallions. Mix together with all ingredients except shrimp.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat precooked shrimp in marinade and let stand in the fridge at least for 15-30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in a salad, on lettuce leaves, with pasta, or on skewers.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '290.jpg', '290-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-08', '23:40:22', 0, 0, 0, '', 661, '167.114.64.97\n185.191.171.34\n192.99.5.225\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n185.191.171.24\n37.57.218.243\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:55ec:84e3:28c1:2730', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6edb40d3f2e8165358f671384c72bb389bd2d1d5', '2020-12-27 04:44:30', 0),
(291, 3, 'Crispy Waffles', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Follow up from my regular waffle recipe for crispier waffles. I use a mini waffle iron, but it makes enough batter for two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Whip egg white until stiff peaks forms and set aside.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #626262;\" /><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\" data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack. You might want to leave the waffle in the waffle maker longer than the regular cooking time for a crispier waffle.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are not eating them right away you can keep them warm and crispy in the oven on 225 F after cooking. If you are making them for another day or a few hours later you can re-heat them in a toaster.<br /><br />Feel free to add 0.5 teaspoon cinnamon and/or a teaspoon vanilla extract.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '291.jpg', '291-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-10', '01:19:52', 0, 0, 0, '', 1282, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n185.191.171.37\n185.191.171.43\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n37.57.218.243\n2a01:4f8:192:3e4::2\n185.191.171.14\n114.119.151.208', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c40f1092fd5b1d94ae1fd27deb597e8ce77d9f05', '2020-12-27 04:45:06', 0),
(292, 3, 'Chinese Dipping Sauce', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'For lettuce wraps, Potstickers or Gyozas.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop scallions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '292.jpg', '292-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-10', '01:31:14', 2, 0, 0, '', 958, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.14\n37.57.218.243', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', '', '9f354d6b8665746ed80f1b495eb19a342306ae63', '2020-12-27 04:45:55', 0),
(293, 3, 'Chinese Chicken Lettuce Wrap (P.F Chang&#039;s)', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I&#039;ve heard that traditionally P.F Chang&#039;s uses oyster sauce in their lettuce wrap. In this recipe, I use hoisin sauce to make it easier and quicker.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Chop onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, onions, scallions, and water chestnuts into small dices.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\nMix sauce ingredients in a bowl and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook chicken in a skillet over medium-high heat.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Towards the end of the cooking time add onion, bell pepper, mushroom, and chestnuts. Cook for 4 minutes or until chicken is done</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add sauce over chicken and let it heat up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over lettuce wraps and dipping sauce. Recipe for dipping sauce here:&nbsp;<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=292&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=292&amp;l=en</a><br /><br />It might seem like a small amount of sauce for such a big serving, but the sauce should only cover the meat and veggies and not overflow the lettuce wraps.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '293.jpg', '293-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-10', '01:39:14', 2, 0, 0, '', 1011, '2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n185.191.171.42\n185.191.171.18\n167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bc4b6d24637c7decdb0a551e4069c394d8e2b9c2', '2020-12-27 04:46:50', 0),
(294, 3, 'Baked Meatballs From Turkey or Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Scandinavian style meatballs without eggs or breadcrumbs. Feel free to substitute ground chicken for ground turkey or beef.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Preheat oven to 400F and f</span>inely dice the vegetables into small pieces.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover a baking sheet with parchment paper or an oven-safe silicone mat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Mix spices and cornstarch in a bowl. Add ground chicken, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and mix. Add water in increments, starting at 10-gram to see if it is enough to get a good consistency.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Shape meatballs using a spoon and place on top of the baking sheet. Bake 10-15 minutes or until done.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\"> zoodles,</a> <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=153\">quick pasta sauce</a>, a salad, or with mashed potatoes.&nbsp;<br /><br />Each serving makes a total of 202-gram meatballs shaped into 8 regular sized meatballs. Consequently, each meatball is then 25 gram and 22.75 calories.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br />Feel free to substitute zucchini and mushroom for other vegetables like bell peppers or carrots.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '294.jpg', '294-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-11', '00:56:08', 23, 0, 0, '', 937, '167.114.64.97\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n185.191.171.35\n2a01:4f8:190:14ed::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2\n185.191.171.3\n192.99.4.163\n185.191.171.1', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:203e:fbab:a807:884', '', 'b23b6e306defcca22cb3e68af93c165319225373', '2020-12-27 04:47:23', 0),
(295, 3, 'Jell-O Mousse', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Pick any sugar free flavored gelatin powder and make it into a high protein mousse. My favorite is raspberry and strawberry.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons water and microwave it for 40-50 second. Whisk Jell-O and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add greek yogurt and Jell-O into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer for about 2-4 minutes, you want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '295.jpg', '295-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-12', '23:46:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 976, '185.191.171.3\n114.119.138.199\n185.191.171.40\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n192.99.4.163\n2a01:4f8:121:4076::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c92952ae3051075b85f4700a309c8dfacadb0d37', '2020-12-24 01:19:34', 0),
(296, 3, 'Chocolate Mousse', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'The ultimate chocolate fix that fits your macros!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bloom your gelatin in a little cold water, about one-two tablespoons. In a separate bowl heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons water and microwave it for 40-50 second. Whisk gelatin and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Add greek yogurt, sugar to taste, cocoa, and gelatin into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer, for about for 2-4 minutes. You want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.<br /><br />Blooming helps completely dissolve the gelatin.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '296.jpg', '296-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-13', '00:02:00', 0, 0, 0, '', 1816, '185.191.171.33\n2a01:4f8:161:806b::2\n2a01:4f8:162:1294::2\n114.119.137.125\n185.191.171.45\n173.208.130.202\n185.191.171.40\n167.114.159.183\n185.191.171.11', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5749538d6452b8cd80c9889350d056cde74dd161', '2020-12-26 01:24:32', 0),
(297, 3, 'Lemon Mousse, Protein Edition', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'My all-time favorite mousse.', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Bloom your gelatin in a little cold water, about one-two tablespoons. In a separate bowl heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons water and microwave it for 40-50 second. Whisk gelatin and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Zest lemon. Add greek yogurt, sugar substitute to taste, lemon juice, lemon zest, and gelatin into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer, for about for 2-4 minutes. You want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use fresh lemon juice! Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.<br /><br />Blooming helps completely dissolve the gelatin.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '297.jpg', '297-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-13', '00:09:15', 0, 0, 0, '', 1157, '185.191.171.11\n185.191.171.10\n2a01:4f8:190:4243::2\n192.99.4.163\n148.251.8.250\n185.191.171.26\n185.191.171.37\n185.191.171.13', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '29d48af82f610a4418a6c3c80083d214c3f5e00b', '2020-12-26 02:38:30', 0),
(298, 3, 'Carrot Cake Waffles', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious way to add more volume to your regular waffles. Makes 6 mini-waffles or two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Grate the carrot. Whip egg white until stiff peaks forms and set aside.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I make five to six 4\" waffles. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">For crispier waffles check out this recipe:&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Feel free to add 0.5 teaspoon cinnamon and/or a teaspoon vanilla extract.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '298.jpg', '298-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-13', '01:33:36', 0, 0, 0, '', 678, '114.119.136.113\n185.191.171.3\n173.208.130.202\n185.191.171.8\n91.137.16.200\n185.191.171.22\n185.191.171.41\n185.191.171.2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', '', '512563ae528f844bb6c9f6218c7d5c7334d32a2c', '2020-12-24 22:53:43', 0),
(299, 3, 'Shredded Chicken Breast', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Great for meal prep, salads, tacos, or any other occasion.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>In a pot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place chicken breast in a pot and fill with enough water to cover it (about one inch of water above the chicken). Add spices or vegetables, I use 0.25 teaspoon salt, dash pepper and/or bay leaf. Place the pot over medium-high heat and let boil for 10-20 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast. The internal temperature of the thickest part should reach 165 F.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125651.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"282\" /></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Slow cooker&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place chicken breast in your slow cooker. Fill with 0.25 cup water or until the chicken breast is slightly covered. You can use chicken broth instead of water. Add salt, pepper, and/or a bay leaf. Cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 7-8 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125525.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"346\" /></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>After chicken is done</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Once done let it cool on a plate or cutting board for a few minutes, but not too long!&nbsp; Shred with a fork and pack away in an airtight container.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #626262;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125739.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"394\" /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Adjust the amount of chicken you use for accurate calorie content. Stays fresh in the fridge for 2-3 days and in the freezer for 2-3 months in airtight containers.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '299.jpg', '299-thumb.jpg', '', '2019-05-15', '00:45:08', 0, 0, 0, '', 810, '167.114.64.97\n192.99.9.25\n2a01:4f8:161:81c1::2\n173.249.30.147\n207.180.224.141\n2a01:4f8:190:51c2::2\n114.119.133.14\n37.57.218.243\n2a01:4f8:190:826b::2', 0, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a44d:8375:25b9:ce3c', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bb67aa011f1a034d0a39f5d6fc81ffe02203f2a7', '2020-12-27 04:48:16', 0);
")
